INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES (673,2,'2012-09-27 01:59:39','2012-09-27 05:59:39','Going home so empty inside.','empty','','publish','open','closed','','empty','','','2012-10-01 22:01:23','2012-10-02 02:01:23','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=673',0,'post','',0),(650,2,'2012-08-27 23:40:56','2012-08-28 03:40:56','Dear Cyndi,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI hope this letter brings you in good faith, good fortune, and times of happiness. I know you might not ever want to hear from me again, but I will give you the benefit of the doubt in the case that it will settle curiosity, peace of mind, or in the very least, interest. Today I was going through a box of old letters and read a few from you, still as crisp and neat as the day I got them. You were sweet to me, open, and understanding. I have a couple memories otherwise, but I think they are merely distortions of my perception at the time due to my hypersensitive emotions. I want you to know that you were (and probably still are) sweet and caring to me. You had a lot of sense and understanding and probably handled our situation exactly as it should have been handled, which is probably not true of the behavior from my end. It\'s been too long for me to truly know for sure, but of what little evidence I have of the communication between you and me, what I\'ve seen doesn\'t look like I treated you reasonably. That\'s not to say that I truly mistreated you--I don\'t think that is true--but I think that I could have been better. Well, I couldn\'t have been better, but I should have been. Had I known any better.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI\'ve learned a lot about myself in the past 6 years, and I can tell you that any way I treated you was not because I was a mean person or that I had bad intentions, but because I cared about you so much and wanted you in my life so badly that I eventually got to the point of desperation which completely distorts our own perception of how to act and how not to act. Regardless of how I acted or you acted or who was right and who was wrong, none of which I remember well enough to know either way, I want to extend an apology to you for anything in between--for what I did, for what I didn\'t do, for what I shouldn\'t have done, and for what I didn\'t know to do. I\'m making these judgements based on the fact that you haven\'t talked to me since then, and clearly had no desire to do so many years ago. I can\'t do much, but I can tell you I\'m sorry. Even if I never was before, I am now.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI was always confused as to why you wouldn\'t talk to me. I\'m sure there was reason for a while, but I had hoped and expected that some time it would fade away and at least move in the positive direction, if only slightly. Yet, it only continued to move in the negative. For a long time, I did what I needed to do to rid myself of any attraction to you, which took many years, believe it or not, and I presume that is what caused so much harm, of all the things we ever went though. I want you to know that I have no feelings of negativity to you in any way, regardless of what that might mean to you. I have many negative memories of us and feelings of hopelessness, but I\'ve shelved them away and dusted off the positive over the years and moved them to the front. I still remember what it was like the first day I met you and the power you had over me and my heart. I was such a helpless young man, and such a slave to my feelings. I still am, really. You were so beautiful then, and I believe that if I knew you today, you still would be. Both inside your heart and outside with your presence.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI really, really hope that you are doing well. I really, really hope that you are happy. I hope that Boston was everything you ever dreamed it was, and I hope that you\'ve found a happy life in what it\'s been after you knew me. You don\'t ever have to want to talk to me again, and that\'s perfectly okay, but I want to offer you a hand as a lost friend and any other benevolence that I can offer. I am still the exact same boy that you once knew, and though I haven\'t changed much, I have certainly grown. And you were a huge part of that. And you gave me years and years of growth, even after I never knew you any more. There was a time in my life, long after you kindly let me out of your life that I didn\'t think I would ever stop struggling with the hole you left in it. And I was always surprised with how that was--I\'m sure I took things way too seriously. But it was mostly for how badly I wanted you in my life, yet that\'s just not how it works. Thank you for treating me how you did. Thank you for pushing me away when you realized you weren\'t happy. Thank you for being down to earth, blunt, and honest. Thank you for standing up for yourself. And most of all, thank you for not putting up with my emotions of desperation. Honestly, you probably put up with them much more than you should have.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI don\'t expect a response, and you certainly don\'t have to, but if it means anything to you and you would like to, I am completely open to hearing from you. Whether it\'s short, long, criticism, openness, small talk, an update, or a giant list of all the things you hated about me--I don\'t care--I will be open to anything and would love to hear from you regardless of what the content is. And if you\'re curious at all as to what my life is like or who I am these days, I will gladly tell you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf anything, I hope this letter is one of encouragement to you. You were such a light in my life and and though you were a very painful light, you taught me a lot and made me feel things I\'ve never felt before. You made me happier than anyone I had ever known. I still remember the feelings you made me feel that were unique in a way that no one has ever made me feel since--because you are your very own unique person that is different from anyone else. If I never hear from you again, I wish you the very best and hope that your life is a wonderful adventure full of twists, turns, surprises, and excitement.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLove from your old friend,\r\n\r\nRussell Strauss','to cyndi','','publish','open','closed','','to-cyndi','','','2012-10-01 22:07:17','2012-10-02 02:07:17','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=650',0,'post','',0),(666,2,'2012-09-17 21:47:23','2012-09-18 01:47:23','I thought my life was going to go one way and then it went another. I’m fine with it most days but then there are certain moments, such as these, when I’m suffocated by the weight of my own failures. I’ve pretended for so long that this part of me was shut off, damaged goods, that it just wasn’t ever going to happen for me. I became resigned and defeated. Content with my discontent.\r\n\r\nThen the fire will spark and I’ll feel cheated. All of a sudden, I want to get what’s owed to me. I want to get more than what I currently have.\r\n\r\nI’m talking here about love, of course. The act of getting it and then sustaining the connection. Growing up, I always knew that I had a lot of love to give. I felt everything; I felt everyone. I’m always placing my hand on a friend’s body out of habit just so I can be closer to them. There’s no such thing as too close. I’m always looking for connections wherever I go.\r\n\r\n<em>Remind me why I’m here. C’mere.</em>\r\n\r\nI imagined my young adult life to be spent in a series of different people’s beds, limbs entangled, light peeking through the window, fingertips going up and down the back to initiate morning sex. I can so clearly visualize the scene: I’m cooking breakfast for someone. Music is wafting through the laptop speakers and I’m watching a man get dressed. I’m watching his ass, the curve of his back, as he gets clothed and moves forward to kiss me goodbye. Then, when he leaves, the energy will get sucked from the room, the spell will be broken, and I’ll need to go get it again.\r\n\r\nSounds familiar, right? Sounds like something that’s plucked from the pages of your life? I know it is because I’ve been studying it. But despite all of my desire and wanting, there’s been no naked backs hanging from the edge of my bed, no quick passionate kisses goodbye while I’m still half-asleep. There’s been nothing.\r\n\r\nBecause of this, I don’t understand the motions of sex and love. I am not a part of the club.\r\n\r\nOf course, a lot of these failures have to do with me. You can only blame others for so long before realizing that you are a part of the problem. Perhaps what’s more adult than wearing your lover’s shirt and cooking breakfast for them in the morning is coming to the realization that you’re screwed up. Something inside of you broke and it’s up to you to fix it.\r\n\r\nHere’s another familiar scene for you: You look around a room that’s full of your friends and realize you are the only one who isn’t spoken for. Everyone else is clutching on to the arm of their partner while your grip on the bottle of wine stiffens.\r\n\r\nAnother one: You go on a family vacation and realize you are the only one who didn’t bring a significant other. You get to sleep on the pullout because it’s only you and it’s better for one person to be uncomfortable rather than two. <em>Actually, I guarantee that I’m the one who will be in more pain BECAUSE I’m alone.</em>\r\n\r\nLast one: A man brushes your shoulder on the subway and your body practically has convulsions. It’s then that you realize that you haven’t been touched in a long time.\r\n\r\nIt’s easy to sit here and ask, “When will I be spoken for? When will I have someone to bring on the family vacation? When will I get used to someone’s touch?”\r\n\r\nWhen will it be my turn to fall in love?\r\n\r\nI don’t know. No one knows. Stop buying the books that tell you when because they’re merely profiting off of your vulnerabilities. Just focus on yourself and pray that the fire never stops sparking. Pray that you never get used to all of this because the second you do, it’s yours forever.','when will it be my turn to fall in love?','','publish','open','closed','','when-will-it-be-my-turn-to-fall-in-love','','','2012-10-01 22:04:04','2012-10-02 02:04:04','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=666',0,'post','',0),(623,2,'2012-07-25 20:21:02','2012-07-26 01:21:02','I believe that God gave me a brain for a reason. God gave me a heart to follow for a reason. He did not simpy put me on this earth to follow rules, but to live life to its fullest.\r\n\r\nAnd life to its fullest means something different for every man. And that\'s why he gave me my head to use to my own advantage. I take what I learn from the Bible very liberally. I do not follow it word for word, nor do I agree with everything it says. Yet even then, I do not think it always leads me in the right direction when I follow it too strictly. There are too many contradictions to do so. God\'s word is not about rules, but about love. Do not misinterpret, I believe the word is a huge source of guidance that every man should look to for every decision he makes, but so many simply do not know how to read it. I\'m exaggerating a little and being a tad disrespectful, but trying to communicate my perspective without being able to easily do so. But what if God added these contradictions that we not listen to everything we are told but to learn from life and follow our hearts? I\'ve certainly learned that had I followed everything the church taught me and tried to live out the prude, closed-minded perspective of today\'s christians, I would not be living life to its fullest. I would be living a life that, to me, could not be its happiest.\r\n\r\nBut I\'ve carefully listened for God. I\'ve squinted my eyes, tried hard to see what\'s right, and attempted to follow after that small speck of light. I\'ve always done my best. And that\'s why I\'m completely happy. That\'s why I\'m completely satisfied with my life and where I am. But what if I don\'t continue to do this in everything that I do?\r\n\r\nI think I\'m coming to a fork in the road. I can decide to learn for myself and do as God has taught me, to follow my heart and take risks, or I can decide to live a sterile and protected life, free of potential hurt, missing out on things I need.\r\n\r\nBut am I just trying to justify a wrong decision? Possibly. Is it likely? Yes. But am I following my heart? Yes. Am I listening to everything that whispers guidance in my direction, trying desperately to figure out what is right? Of course I am.\r\n\r\nI may not make the right decision, but I will certainly make the decision that I believe is right, closely trying to live my life as God has taught me in order to live my life to its fullest potential.\r\n\r\nFollowing my heart one-hundred percent of the way.','the way i was made','','inherit','open','closed','','601-revision-9','','','2012-07-25 20:21:02','2012-07-26 01:21:02','',601,'http://journal.rruffles.com/601-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(4,2,'2004-01-18 21:46:00','2004-01-18 21:46:00','<p>Today was Sunday! Woohoo! I love Sundays, but today wasn\'t really that great. When I go tto church I took a walk on the trail in the woods. (My parent\'s don\'t go to my church any more. ugh.... So I have to get to church early so that they can get ot heir church on time) Kellie and I were very uptight this morning when we first got there. After we got through with that, the big people church was much better. It helped me loosen up. I was really stressed out about everything. After churc, I tried to see if I could go to Kellie\'s house(dream on) until Fuel, but I couldn\'t of course. When we got home I put a bunch of pictures in a picture album I got for Christams. That took an hour or so. Then I ate and I wanted to get on the computer after I was finished. In the end, I ended up kicking my brother and he yelled and woke them up and I got in BIG trouble. Then I had to pay him 10 bucks for something...it\'s a long story for another day. Eventually, we left for Fuel and that wasn\'t too bad. Hopefully I\'ll actually do it right this semester. I doubt I\'ll get it right this time, I never do. Anyway, after that we got out and Kellie was in the parking lot. She was really upset and wouldn\'t talk to me. I am upposed to be calling her now. I\'ll do that when I\'m done. Then we went to eat at Wendy\'s like we always do. Me and and Chuck REALLY wanted to run across the street to Moe\'s but we couldn\'t. After I got home, I started talking to Karyn and Annie. It was great. They really listen what I have to say. Well, that\'s my day. I need to go call Kellie.</p>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Godspeed.</p>','Jan. 18','','publish','open','open','','jan-18','','','2004-01-18 21:46:00','2004-01-18 21:46:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=4',0,'post','',4),(5,2,'2004-01-20 22:02:00','2004-01-20 22:02:00','It\'s Tuesday. Time for bed, actually. Nobody goes to bed at the same time everytnight anyway. At least, I don\'t. I definately don\'t. I can barely get into bed period. Anyway, I forgot what I was going to say. It looks like soon I\'ll be going to sleep and getting right back up again. Then I will struggle to get on the bus on time and minutes later be at school. I will sit in class all day, trying to do work or talking to my \"friends\". Then, I come home and within minutes, it will be time for rest once again. Figures, but I don\'t mind. I love my life anyway. Sometimes I wonder if I could ever ask for more. God has given me so much. Even things that I don\'t care about that are amazing. Just like the wind. It is most likely not a life changing experience, but an amazing thing. Think about it. Just being able to go out into your yard and lie in the grass. Nobody does that, but when you think about it, senses are amazing. Those are just the little things. Huge things like my relationships, I can\'t even imagine why God would give someone like me something so amazing. I love it. Sometimes they are hard,  but always worth it. I could never understand why people say \"love sucks\". No one can live without love. I couldn\'t live without my friends, family, teachers, youth leaders, and many other people that have changed my life. Most of all, I live off of God\'s love. Everyone does. Most of them don\'t even know it, which is heart breaking. I could never imagine living without God. That would be absolutely horrible. \r\n\r\nYesterday, was very fun. I got to go to Discover Mills with many of my friends even though some of my best ones couldn\'t come. Actually, they were all at Jacob\'s house. I don\'t understand it. They always leave me out of everything they do. I asked Derek to come over Sunday night. He siad he couldn\'t. Instead he decides to go to Jacob\'s house...along with Chuck. Nobody wanted to come to my house. Nobody wanted me to come. But still, I got to go to Discover Mills with people that don\'t leave me out of things and do care about me. I got to spend the day with, Kellie, Chris (the one guy I can talk to), Karyn (one of my newer friends that also cares about me), and Annie. It was fun, but much different than I expected. Annie and Karyn didn\'t really get ot meet any of my real friends. I think it would have been different if we had gone after church, with more people from church.\r\n\r\nOver the last week Kellie has been really upset about me talking to Karyn. I don\'t really understand why she cares so much. I can see her worrying, but she was totally out of hand. She got really upset last night. I will pray and ask anyone else to do the same. I wish she would understand that I\'m really not attracted to anyone but her, whatsoever. \r\n\r\nToday was okay. I was really tired from staying up late. I want to get to bed early tonight, but I guess it\'s too late for that. I went to school which was the same as always, but I had Computer Science which made the day seem much longer. I have CREATE tomorrow, which is good. That will get me excited. Also, we have the Trail. I will have to be a car rider, which last week I forgot(hahaha). I got on the bus and the jerkface bus driver wouldn\'t let me off when I remembered. My parents had to come pick me up at my house, which was cool because I didn\'t have to go straight there but still got there early. I told Karyn to remind me tomorrow. I hope she remembers becuase I will most likely forget. I really want her to come to the Trail sometime. She told me that she is Catholic, which made me wonder. I don\'t think that there would really be that much of a difference even though it seems like there would be. I want to ask Tait about it. Either way, I think she would love it, as long as she isn\'t shy. It looks like she wants to come ot Sharptop. I\'ll have to ask her about that. If she is going to come, I need to get her signed up. It will be fun. I just hope Kellie doesn\'t freak out. I told her, and she didn\'t seem to mind much. \r\n\r\nWell, I think it\'s time to retire for tonight. Pray that I\'m not tired in the morning. That would be awesome. Goodnight and\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                                             Godspeed','Excited About Nothing','','publish','open','open','','excited-about-nothing','','','2004-01-20 22:02:00','2004-01-20 22:02:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=5',0,'post','',9),(6,2,'2004-01-21 22:16:00','2004-01-21 22:16:00','Today was okay. I had CREATE, but tomorrow that means I have Computer Science. Oh joy...  Oh well,  maybe I\'ll learn something. Even if I only learn one thing t