d that I thought was theirs (I had been there before, but I wasn\'t EXACTLY sure where it was) and made sure it was theirs and headed down the road. I got nervous everytime I saw a cop car because I wasn\'t wearing a helmet and I think that\'s against the law but oh well. I was gonna put Micah\'s note in his mailbox(I made a note that said \"I KNOW WHERE YOU LIVE MICAH!\" hahahah) but there was a cop  that lived across the street so I was hesitant because opening someone\'s mailbox is against the law, ya know. We rode down past Chance\'s house and for the blink of an eye I saw this guy sitting in a chair beside Chance\'s house. Before I could think (or do anything else for that matter) I screamed CHANCE! I realized it was Chance and we rode over to say hey. He was talking to Emily. I figured we would just go by his house, drop off the stalker not and leave, but Chance just HAPPENED to be outside hahaha. He said, \"I think Micah is home\" and we ran over and I got to meet Micah! Woohoo! I said something about not opening Micah\'s mailbox becuase of the cop and Chance said it was just a fat guy that ate (I just typed \"opened donuts all the time\" hahah I hate no idea why) donuts all the time. Anyway, so we talked for a while and said our goodbyes and then left. hahah Micah had just gotten home and he said that he was riding down the road and saw three guys on bikes and started to wonder hahaha, it was pretty funny. So Chance, next time you are coming to MY house! hahah It will be awesome. So yeah, I had a ton of fun today. After we came home, we ate Chinese food and it was really good. Especially after the really long bike ride. Fourteen miles...\r\n\r\nIt was awesome. We\'ll do it again sometime. I hope.... I don\'t think my parents would be happy if they found out where we went (across 316 nudge nudge).','YAY','','publish','open','open','','yay','','','2004-04-11 11:23:00','2004-04-11 11:23:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=112',0,'post','',9),(113,2,'2004-