ar, and my journal. I can\'t believe this. It sucks. I will have a lot of typing to do when I get back [actually I found a computer at the college- my grandpa lives next to Emory University], not to mention I get to makeup that huge standardized Math test when I get back. \r\n\r\nHow is it that people that don\'t even have a Bible, who\'ve never even read on before, can have as MUCH faith as- or MORE faith than- I do?\r\n\r\nGod Speed, Russell\r\n\r\n-date: 4/28/04  -time: 6:25  -place: Grandparent\'s House\r\n\r\nDay 1:\r\n\r\nLife is hard, yet I stand strong. God is FOR me, not against me.\r\n\r\nWell, looks like I finally get some rest. I\'m exhausted. \r\n\r\n\"Well mom, I\'m having a great time here at camp Green Lake...\" Ever read that book? That\'s <b>exactly</b> what I feel like. \r\n\r\nI got here this morning. My grandpa took me around the yard for awhile, then we came in to eat. I can\'t really remember it very well. I need sleep. After we ate, he went to take a nap, so I had an hour to play or mess around with whatever. I tried to figure out Giants that Garrick had taught me. Melissa called so I talked to her for a long time. [that made me feel <b>so</b> much better, but it really wasn\'t that long] I wish she was here. After he woke up, we went to get medecine, plants, and other things. We went to this really ghetto Wal-Mart that was from the 90\'s. [it was crazy I tell you] It even had one of those circus food cart things outside. It was crazy. On the way home, he had forgotten some medecine, so we had to go back. We came home, and went out to till. This isn\'t power tools I\'m talking about. We did it the old school way. We also put up this bird feeder [that was earlier in the day I just forgot about it] This will be one hard week. I just want to talk to my -cough- friends.\r\nMood: mellow, hungry, lonely\r\nMusic: Fractions - Emery\r\n\r\n<i>are you listening?\r\nwe write a thousand pages, \r\nthey\'re torn and on the floor,\r\nheadlights hammer the windows, \r\nwe\'re locked behind these doors,\r\nand we are never leaving, this place is part of us,\r\nand all these scenes repeating are cold to the touch,\r\nmy hands seem to deceive me,\r\nwhen I\'m nervous or when I\'m healthy,\r\nthe scenery\'s all drawn,\r\nthey hang here from the walls dear,\r\npainting pictures, bleeding colors,\r\nblanket the windows,\r\nsometimes it gets so hard to breathe,\r\nyour eyes see right through me</i>\r\n\r\n\r\n[I have to finish the rest later folks.]','To make a long story short, I got mad.','','publish','open','open','','to-make-a-long-story-short-i-got-mad','','','2004-05-01 14:47:00','2004-05-01 14:47:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=151',0,'post','',1),(152,2,'2004-05-01 20:14:00','2004-05-01 20:14:00','Get out of my yard and give me my chicken!!!!','Five Iron Frenzy Day!','','publish','open','open','','five-iron-frenzy-day','','','2004-05-01 20:14:00','2004-05-01 20:14:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=152',0,'post','',4),(153,2,'2004-05-06 16:41:00','2004-05-06 16:41:00','<img src=\"http://a.1asphost.com/BuddyofSponge/LiveJournal/As%20Your%20Voice%20Fades.jpg\" alt=\"\">\r\nEmery - As Your Voice Fades\r\n<a href=\"www.theweaksend.com\">www.theweaksend.com</a>\r\nI\'m grounded. Can\'t use the computer for a long time. Don\'t ask because I don\'t know. I\'ll talk to you guys later. I love you.\r\n\r\nBy the way, I made that picture.','Emery - As Your Voice Fades','','publish','open','open','','emery-as-your-voice-fades-2','','','2004-05-06 16:41:00','2004-05-06 16:41:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=153',0,'post','',7),(154,2,'2004-05-07 14:08:00','2004-05-07 14:08:00','I am at school. In Social Studies. Mrs. Layfield is cool. I\'mdoing some project on MLKJ. Chance and Ryan come over tonight! wooohooo!','School','','publish','open','open','','school','','','2004-05-07 14:08:00','2004-05-07 14:08:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=154',0,'post','',0),(155,2,'2004-05-07 14:16:00','2004-05-0