r\n\r\nI believed in what I hoped for,\r\nAnd I hope in things unseen,\r\nI had wings and dreams could soar,\r\nI just don\'t feel like flying anymore\r\n\r\nToday was the last day of school. It was kinda weird. Can\'t really say how. It didn\'t feel like the end. I know I will still see everyone. I am crazy though. When I got off the bus my mom was up on the porch singing or something. It was kind of strange. Seems like she\'s more excited about it than us. I ate or something like that, then Garrick called. He wanted to know if I was going to go to the mall with them. Davis was goign to go to the pool instead. Chance was going to baseball. I felt it kind of pointless. I found out Garrick went anyway with someone else, it made me feel bad. Not for me, but him. I called Will and headed over to his house. I forgot that I had told Melissa I would call her back in 5 minutes. I don\'t know how that happened, I\'m always thinking of her. Oh well, I called her back like a long time later and found out she was at Micah\'s game. Micah was on first base so I wanted her to tell him that I said hey but she wouldn\'t because she\'s a bully. I told her to call me back when the game was over so I could talk to him but she didn\'t. It made me sad. \r\n\r\nLord, search my heart,\r\nCreate in me something clean,\r\nDandelions, You flowers in these weeds\r\n\r\nAfter talking to her, we installed the sims and I played that while Will watching that dumb American Idol show. Melissa kept setting our house on fire. It reminded me of when Chance and I were playing and people would come to our house, pee in the road, then have seisures. It was weird. I kept having to buy new ovens. Then I threw the fireman in the pool. It was quite amusing. Eventually, I went home and my dad got all ticked off for me being on the phone past nine on a summer night, so it made me mad and I was like screw you I\'m getting online. So I\'m here now. After that, I had to take out the trash. I guess it didn\'t matter that it was 11 o\'clock at night. My brother took out one this morning. I had to take out 4. It made me mad. It was fun anyway though, so it didn\'t matter. I\'m already enjoying my summer on the first night.\r\n\r\nHere\'s my heart,\r\nLet it be forever Yours,\r\nOnly You can make every new day seem so new\r\n\r\nI was calling Jacob all night to see if he could come over, but I could never get him. Chance couldn\'t either because his mom wouldn\'t let him. Hopefully, they can both come over tomorrow night. Jacob told me there is an Awkward Romance concert at Crossroads tomorrow at 6 for free. Hopefully we\'re going to that. I don\'t want to miss Hebron but oh well. That is every week.\r\n\r\nI\'m sorry I haven\'t been updating you guys on everythign lately. It\'s just that I\'m not allowed to use the computer, so I\'ve been journaling in my real journals. If you ever see me with one of them you can read it. Anyway, nothing big has really happened. My sister is in the Czech Republic. I hope things are going well for her there. She mailed of two cents. It was kinda cool. And the two ticket things but I didn\'t bother to read it so I didn\'t really know what they were. I\'m lazy. I haven\'t even read her emails. And she\'s my favorite person. They are long. \r\n\r\nI have a missions trip next week. I really have no idea what it will be like. I\'m just glad because it will be fun with Jacob. And the Joshes. And the other guys. I\'m not expecting anything. I probably am. I just don\'t know it. Pray for me.\r\n\r\nMy Lord, how long to sing this song? \r\nAnd my Lord, how muchmore of this pretending to be strong?\r\n\r\nI\'ve been listening to mewithoutyou tonight. They are awesome. When I heard them live I didn\'t like it at all. They\'re speaking french in this song. Bullet to Binary.\r\n\r\nI know I said nothing big has happened but whoops. We had a wedding at our house. It was good. It was POURING. There was a huuuge thunderstorm. Luckily, by the time the wedding came, that evening, all there were was white clouds. I got to invite Melissa. It was fun. \r\n\r\nI\'m running out of things to say. If it doesn\'t come out without forcing it, there\'s no reason to write it. That\'s kind of what I\'ve been doing in my real journal. I think it\'s just because it\'s almost finished. \r\n\r\n\r\nI talk to you guys later.\r\nYou can email me. RussellStrauss@hotmail.com\r\n\r\nGod Speed, \r\nRussell','','','publish','open','open','','166','','','2004-05-26 03:22:00','2004-05-26 03:22:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=166',0,'post','',7),(167,2,'2004-05-26 14:28:00','2004-05-26 14:28:00','Je leverai les yeux a toi- \r\nJ\'ai change cent foi de nom \r\nJe leverai les yeux a toi- \r\nJe n\'ai pas d\'espoir.','','','publish','open','open','','167','','','2004-05-26 14:28:00','2004-05-26 14:28:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=167',0,'post','',8),(168,2,'2004-05-29 19:47:00','2004-05-29 19:47:00','I am leaving for a missions trip tomorrow morning. I\'ll be gone for a week. Pray for me guys.','','','publish','open','open','','168','','','2004-05-29 19:47:00','2004-05-29 19:47:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=168',0,'post','',7),(169,2,'2004-06-08 19:32:00','2004-06-08 19:32:00','<img src=\"http://www.zambooie.com/images/julianatheory/julianatheorybanner.gif\">\r\n<img scr=\"http://www.zambooie.com/images/mewithoutyou/mwybanner.jpg\">\r\n<img src=\"http://www.zambooie.com/product_images/mewithoutyou/mwys100.jpg\">\r\n\r\n<marquee> woah woah </marquee>','hey you','','publish','open','open','','hey-you','','','2004-06-08 19:32:00','2004-06-08 19:32:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=169',0,'post','',4),(170,2,'2004-06-10 01:56:00','2004-06-10 01:56:00','<img src=\"http://img38.photobucket.com/albums/v118/BuddyofSponge/LiveJournal/Straight_hair_for_LJ.jpg\">\r\n\r\nBrittany straightened my hair at DC. It was awesome.','','','publish','open','open','','170','','','2004-06-10 01:56:00','2004-06-10 01:56:00','',0,'http