In your tuxedo suit.\r\nI will give it a name.\r\nLower your defenses.\r\nLower your casket.\r\nOpen the door and open your grave.\r\nMurder.\r\nNow you’re doing the waltz with your murderer.\r\nMediocrity is the killer.\r\nYou find yourself helpless.\r\nChrist is not a fashion, fleeting away.\r\nHe laid emeralds in her eyes,\r\nBut I’d already tried a bracelet made of gold\r\nAnd a scarlet thread around her wrist.\r\nEverything was wrong so we sang sentimental songs.\r\nOh how seldom we belong but how elegant our kiss.\r\nWe painted crooked lines\r\nBut danced in perfect time to a love so much refined,\r\nWe know not what it is until like a dullen wine we pour into a grief know before\r\nBut never quite like this.\r\nAll I know now is regret,\r\nIt follows like a silhouette along the cobblestone behind us,\r\nBut has nothing to say except to innocently ask,\r\nIts voice delicate as glass,\r\nDo you see me when we pass? \r\nBut I continue on my way. \r\n\r\nI was once the wine,\r\nAnd you the wineglass.\r\n\r\n\r\nI\'m not the boy that I once was,\r\nYet, I\'m not the man I\'ll be.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe cure for pain is in the pain,\r\nso it\'s there that you\'ll find me.\r\nUntil again I forget,\r\nand again he reminds me,\r\n\"Hear my voice in your head,\r\nand think of me kindly.\"\r\nYou\'d only make the softest sound,\r\nlike sugar pouring into tea.\r\nDarling let your Self pour down\r\nand dissolve into the Love\r\nwho revealed himself there quietly to me...\r\n\r\n(Jesus have mercy on us.)\r\n\r\n\r\nI will raise the eyes has you- \r\nI HAVE changes hundred name faiths \r\nI will raise the eyes has you- \r\nI have not hope.\r\n\r\n\r\nOn my playlist, Copeland is right after Norma Jean. It\'s a very interesting experience.','Christ is not a fashion, fleeting away when you are done with him.','','publish','open','open','','christ-is-not-a-fashion-fleeting-away-when-you-are-done-with-him','','','2004-06-14 01:54:00','2004-06-14 01:54:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=174',0,'post','',0),(175,2,'2004-06-14 14:52:00','2004-06-14 14:52:00','Well guys,  nothing is going right. But anyway, Chuck is backing out of Wislere  and I can\'t  afford to  pay 14 dollars a  month so if any of you guys  want to help please do.\r\n\r\nWislere is our little pimp in Haiti that we sponsor. It\'s 35 dollars a  month and my brother, a few  of my guy friends, and I split it up and pay it every month (7$). We need some help, Chuck and Levi are quitting so if any of you guys want to help, we need it. All you have to do is stick  it in your mailbox once a month. \r\n\r\nSomebody come to my house tonight.\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nIf you find yourself here on my side of town\r\nI\'d pray that you\'d come to my door\r\nTalk to me like you don\'t know what we ever fought about\r\nCause I don\'t remember anymore\r\nI just know that she warms my heart\r\nAnd knows were all my imperfections are\r\nAnd she said that I was the brightest little firefly in her jar\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://bunnysnoog.cyborgcow.net/henry12.gif\"\r\nalign=left><a href=\"http://bunnysnoog.cyborgcow.net/index.html\">\r\nI adopted a cute lil\' gothy fetus\r\nfrom Fetusmart! Hooray fetus! </a>','Like an orphan needs a home once again.','','publish','open','open','','like-an-orphan-needs-a-home-once-again','','','2004-06-14 14:52:00','2004-06-14 14:52:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=175',0,'post','',5),(176,2,'2004-06-15 13:22:00','2004-06-15 13:22:00','<img src=\"http://images.quizilla.com/1033888926_ffschizoid.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"HASH(0x8ab4edc)\"><br />schizoid\r\n<br /><br /><a href=\"http://quizilla.com/users/rosiekins/quizzes/Which%20Personality%20Disorder%20Do%20You%20Have%3F/\"> <font size=\"-1\">Which Personality Disorder Do You Have?</font></a><br /> <font size=\"-3\">brought to you by <a href=\"http://quizilla.com\">Quizilla</a></font>','','','publish','open','open','','176','','','2004-06-15 13:22:00','2004-06-15 13:22:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=176',0,'post','',0),(177,2,'2004-06-15 14:11:00','2004-06-15 14:11:00','<img src=\"http://a.1asphost.com/BuddyofSponge/LiveJournal/Grave.jpg\">','Memphis Will be Laid to Waste','','publish','open','open','','memphis-will-be-laid-to-waste','','','2004-06-15 14:11:00','2004-06-15 14:11:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=177',0,'post','',13),(178,2,'2004-06-20 02:44:00','2004-06-20 02:44:00','<img src=\"http://linux.toothandnail.com/controlpanel/uploads/featured_artist/supertones9748.jpg\"><br /><img src=\"http://linux.toothandnail.com/controlpanel/uploads/releases/supertones_revenge_1207961.jpg\">Today was cool. I woke up at 1:18. After I got up, I wandered around a little, ate something, then headed out to mow the grass. I found out that I had filled the mower with kerosene last time (not good) so we had to do all this crap then go get gas and everything. Eventually I got it mowed and everything. \r\n\r\nBy the way, I\'ve been at Atlanta Fest for the last few days. Aaron acted really dumb when I told him. I don\'t like him. My faith is not his buisnass. Now Tait is a different story. He is awesome, I wish we could talk more. Anyway, I bought a bunch of CDs and feel really spoiled even though I earned all of the money working but I still feel spoiled for some reason. I got the new Supertones CD so it\'s all good.\r\n\r\nI mowed the grass so now 234 down, about 120 to go. After I mowed, I went to Mitch\'s house because it was my first chance to go see him since he got back (4 days ago - Tuesday). It was awesome. He hasn\'t changed. A little rough at first, but it was great. I walked there because my front tire to my bike was busted (I think from when Chuck and I went to the falls) and searched all over and none of them seemed to be home, so I headed back home. I said to myself, \"Self, there is still hope, you might see them drive by on the way home.\" I really did think that because it has happened quite a few times. As I was breasting (ha! I couldn\'t help myself, that seriously is a real way to use that word) the last hill, just about to make to my road, I saw a black truck turn. My heart jumped. Their truck is so reckonizable. Not only because it is unique (big black harley pickup truck with flames on the side. not huge ones just little line things), but also because I have riden in it so many times. As they got closer I saw it was them (even though I knew it was them the second they turned the corner) and I was so excited, yet still paniced because I didn\'t know what they (Mitch and his dad- Mitch\'s dad is awesome. He almost just as much a friend as Mitch is) would do or say. I told him I had gone to their house and they weren\'t there and they said they went to my house on the way home and neither of us were home and then said \"Hop in!\" Mitch\'s hair a REALLY a lot longer. We got back and scooped poop. I brought a bathing suit since he has a pool and asked him if he wanted to swim and he did (enthusiastically which surprised me, not that he doesn\'t like swimming or anything) so we went swimming. First thing, we saw a frog so we got him. We played with him the whole hour and a half or however long it was that we swam. His name was Angus. I wanted to name him Hubert, though. Mitch\'s dad came out and asked us if we wanted to go to Waffle house, so that\'s what we did. It was a regualr thing we do. None of you really know about Mitch, but he has been one of my best friends ever since the missions trip to New York we went on two years ago. I haven\'t said anything about him because ever since I\'ve had this journal, he\'s been in California, living with his biological family. He\'s going back because he hates it here and loves it there but it\'s okay because I know we will pick up exactly where we left off. It was so much fun hahahaha the entire night I was like \"Hey sponge Buddy (that\'s what we call each other, it\'s where my screen name came from if you didn\'t know that-Sponge Buddy was taken) remember when we did this and this and this and this and this?\" hahahahah there were SO many things that came back to me. After he leaves and comes back again I\'m goign to say \"Hey Sponge Buddy, remember when I came over and we swam and had Angus and divorced and everything\" hahahahahhah I think Angus got tired of getting chucked across the pool and being a circus frog and doing the high dive and escaping from prison and swimming hahahahah. When we got out he was either really comfortable with us holding him or really tired. ha, Mitch hasn\'t changed ONE bit. I love him. \r\n\r\n\r\nhahaha \r\n\r\nTime for bed. I have to wake up early tomorrow. Three and a half hours of sleep, here I come. I love all of you guys. Call me today(Sunday), Chance. If you don\'t, I will be forced to.','The cure for pain is in the pain.','','publish','open','open','','the-cure-for-pain-is-in-the-pain','','','2004-06-20 02:44:00','2004-06-20 02:44:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=178',0,'post','',1),(179,2,'2004-06-20 23:44:00','2004-06-20 23:44:00','YAY! I finally got this awesome banner thing up that I\'ve wanted on here for ages! Check it out.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n^\r\nl\r\nl','She simply will not die.','','publish','open','open','','she-simply-will-not-die','','','2004-06-20 23:44:00','2004-06-20 23:44:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=179',0,'post','',7),(180,2,'2004-06-27 01:11:00','2004-06-27 01:11:00','TYPE YOUR NAME WITH YOUR...\r\n\r\n\r\nNOSE: Ruswsell\r\nElBOW: RRTTuusasaewkllk\r\nTOUNGE: XRusse ll\r\nCHIN: eruisasaesrk,,k\r\nFEET: r8uededell\r\nEYES CLOSED AND ONE FINGER: russse[[\r\nBACK OF YOUR HAND: russell\r\nPALM: russell\r\nMOUSE: um...I don\'t have a mouse\r\nWRIST: russell\r\n\r\n\r\nThe screen kept getting in the way.\r\n\r\n\r\nI want someone to share my smile,\r\nShare the pain,\r\nTo be there when the sea turns gray','Let us die Let us die','','publish','open','open','','let-us-die-let-us-die','','','2004-06-27 01:11:00','2004-06-27 01:11:00','',0,'htt