 01:24:00','2004-07-13 01:24:00','<marquee scrollamount=\"1\" direction=\"up\"><font size=\"2\">When I was young, the smallest trick of light,\r\nCould catch my eye,\r\nThen life was new and every new day,\r\nI thought that I could fly.\r\nI believed in what I hoped for,\r\nAnd I hoped for things unseen,\r\nI had wings and dreams could soar,\r\nI just don\'t feel like flying anymore.\r\nWhen the stars threw down their spears,\r\nWatered Heaven with their tears,\r\nBefore words were spoken,\r\nBefore eternity.\r\n\r\nDear Father, I need you,\r\nYour strength my heart to mend.\r\nI want to fly higher,\r\nEvery new day again.\r\n\r\nWhen I was small, the furthest I could reach,\r\nWas not so high,\r\nThen I thought the world was so much smaller,\r\nFeeling that I could fly.\r\nThrough distant deeps and skies,\r\nBehind infinity,\r\nBelow the face of Heaven,\r\nHe stoops to create me.\r\n\r\nDear Father, I need you,\r\nYour strength my heart to mend.\r\nI want to fly higher,\r\nEvery new day again.\r\n\r\nMan versus himself.\r\nMan versus machine.\r\nMan versus the world.\r\nMankind versus me.\r\nThe struggles go on,\r\nThe wisdom I lack,\r\nThe burdens keep pilling\r\nUp on my back.\r\nSo hard to breathe,\r\nTo take the next step.\r\nThe mountain is high,\r\nI wait in the depths.\r\nYearning for grace,\r\nAnd hoping for peace.\r\nDear God...\r\nIncrease.\r\nHealing hands of God have mercy on our unclean souls once again.\r\nJesus Christ, light of the world burning bright within our hearts forever.\r\nFreedom means love without condition,\r\nwithout a beginning or an end.\r\nHere\'s my heart, let it be forever Your\'s,\r\nOnly You can make every new day seem so new.','','','publish','open','open','','195','','','2004-07-13 01:24:00','2004-07-13 01:24:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=195',0,'post','',0),(196,2,'2004-07-13 11:41:00','2004-07-13 11:41:00','<marquee scrollamount=\"1\" direction=\"up\"><font size=\"2\">\r\nHow did I get here all tied up\r\nI\'m all tired up\r\nI never noticed or cared that much\r\nOr cared that much\r\nComplaceny has gotten the best of me\r\nAnd the best of me is forgotten\r\nBeneath the sea of what I\'ve become\r\nAnd all that I\'ve done I hope that it counts\r\nI\'d rather be knocked down\r\nThen to be knocked out\r\nSo I\'ll let go of what I know,\r\nOf what I\'ve learned here in the past twenty years\r\nMy heart is frozen with meaningless motions\r\nSo I\'ll hold onto you\r\nAnd all that I\'ve done\r\nI hope that it counts\r\nI\'ve been knocked down\r\nBut I\'m not knocked <b>out</b>\r\nAnd I\'m at the bottom\r\nCan\'t get out\r\nI\'ve been knocked down\r\nBut not knocked out\r\nNot knocked out\r\n<font size=\"3\"><b>And I will sing at the top of my lungs\r\nI will dance even if I\'m the only one</b></font>\r\nAnd i hope that we\'ll never be apart\r\nAnd I will sing and I hope it heals my heart\r\nYeah I hope it heals my heart\r\nHow did I get here?\r\nSave me from this.','I guess I was waiting for something better to come.','','publish','open','open','','i-guess-i-was-waiting-for-something-better-to-come','','','2004-07-13 11:41:00','2004-07-13 11:41:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=196',0,'post','',5),(197,2,'2004-07-14 12:48:00','2004-07-14 12:48:00','I went to Mary\'s house today. It was ssssUPER fun. She said that she had a piano lesson when I was leaving around 1:40. I was like pooop because I would only get to stay for about half an hour. So, we\'re swimming for awhile and I realize it has been way, way longer than thirty minutes. I discovered that it wasn\'t Mary\'s lesson, it was her little sister\'s, Erica. So I\'m like \"It\'s coo, it\'s coo.\". Her mom had already taken her sister and she let me stay because her brother and sister were with us. We went inside and started making dinner and stuff because she had to do that. It reminded me of the time I almost caught the kitchen on fire, which wasn\'t very long ago. Afterwards, she played piano for me, on which I will say she is absolutely marvelous. I couldn\'t believe it. Anyway, she got her little brother\'s guitar which didn\'t go too smoothely. It was out of tune so I didn\'t really know what to do. She seemed to understand somewhat. We finished making dinner and stuff and we went outside, I don\'t even remember what for, but I ended up fixing the seat of her bike and pumping up her tires. Random. It was so funny, she was just riding around with totally flat tires. I must say though, that was one heck of a workout. Then she noticed the thing wasn\'t in the tire all of the way, so it ended up being a lot easier than how it seemed. I had ridden my bike to her house. Her older sister had tried to get her drivers license that day and failed so she was piiiiissssssed. I thought she was going to murder me. It made me feel bad for Mary because she was being so nice to her nonetheless. Her dad came hoem so I met him, and then left again. We went to see the chickens it was so ROCKIN. I wish I had chickens. We also went into the little loft thing which was SO cool. It had a tin roof, so I dreamed of coming out on a rainy winter night and sleeping there. It would be so cool. After that, we looked at picture because there were like a trillion of them. They had gone to Wyoming. She has the most talkative little sister I have ever met. We ate dinner and stuff and I helped clean up. Dinner was so noisy (there are 7 kids and two parents) hahaha it was so much fun. We went outside and tried to talk for a bit, but all 25 of her little siblings were attacking us and wouldn\'t leave us alone. Eventually they started talking about poop and stuf so we told them to run through the field to see who could be the best indian so they all ran screaming through the field. It was the most hilarious thing I had seen all week. I swear her little brother John is ADD. For those of you who were at Starlight with us, he was the one attacking us.\r\n\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://img3.imgspot.com/u/04/195/05/RyanandJohn.JPG\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEventually, we made a run for the truck to hide in the bed of the truck. Surprisingly (right), they found us in about 15 seconds. Then we ran inside and back out onto the deck and yet again, they all followed. Then Mary got her parents attention and they got them away. Then of course, John went outside and around up the stairs and all and his dad yelled at him. Then he found a secret door leading out onto the deck and we thought next he was going to repel out of a window. It was okay though because we got to talk. Her mom came out and told us her sister and her boyfriend were watching a movie downstairs. So, we went down there and started watching it with them. It was Zoolander. We watched it for a few minutes, and she obviously was uncomefortable. It was PG-13. I didn\'t think it was too bad, but eventually she told me that she wanted to watch a different movie. That definaetly makes me look up to her. I wish I had the same innocence and bravery as her. Even though it was only in front of her sister, I still look up to her. So we went up stairs and started watching a different movie, but then my mom called and yelled at me for staying so late. It was dark, so she yelled at me. Luckily, they took me home and they only talked to me for five minutes. \r\n\r\n\r\nI had a <i>wonderful</i> day. Thank you, Mary.','ME WITHOUT YOU','','publish','open','open','pickle','me-without-you','','','2004-07-14 12:48:00','2004-07-14 12:48:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=197',0,'post','',1),(198,2,'2004-07-14 14:22:00','2004-07-14 14:22:00','Conehead to the Xtreme:\r\n<img src=\"http://img3.imgspot.com/u/04/195/17/Conehead.jpg\">\r\n\r\nI love this picture of Jacob:\r\n<img src=\"http://img3.imgspot.com/u/04/195/17/Bench.jpg\">\r\n\r\nCharlie\'s angels:\r\n<img src=\"http://img3.imgspot.com/u/04/195/17/CharliesAngels.jpg\">\r\n\r\nMy friend Derek:\r\n<img src=\"http://img3.imgspot.com/u/04/195/17/Derek.jpg\">\r\n\r\nWe didn\'t like Rachael:\r\n<img sr