reck. Everything happens for a reason. I\'m so glad God has been watching over all of us.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn America it\'s wonderful,\r\nAll you have to do is fake it.\r\nOwn anything you want,\r\nAll you have to do is take it.\r\nLive for today, don\'t think about tomorrow,\r\nHave a good time in America-Gomorrah.\r\n\r\n\r\nLast night we stayed up really late talking about scary stuff and dangerous stuff and how one tiny thing can change anything and all that stuff. Will and Jesse got mad at me because I started talking about Signs. \r\n\r\n\r\nToday, we went to church (not like we ever don\'t), and I forgot my Bible. It made me sad. It\'s not like it\'s unholy or anything to not bring your Bible to church, it\'s just I don\'t like that church, but I love my Bible, and I need something to do during it. Anyway, we came home and my dad wanted to find one of those new QT\'s, so we went to like 5 or 6 QT\'s on the way home from church. I got one of those things where you make a milkshake. It was lame. And very expensive. I wouldn\'t suggest it to anyone. But it\'s okay. Because I didn\'t pay for it. mwahahaha! So we finally got home, and I step out of the car and stand there for a second because, if you don\'t know me, I like to take my time. Very slow, there was no reason to rush. It\'s not like there was anyone online waiting for me to come home and get on. :-(  \r\nYeah, so anyway, I stood there for a second and I heard a bug, and suddenly the back of my left arm, below my shoulder started stinging like caaaRAZY. A stupid wasp stung me. I was just standing there. It made me mad.\r\nI HOPE IT \r\n\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://img4.imgspot.com/u/04/199/21/Dies.jpg\">\r\n\r\n\r\nI went inside and told my mom and she started FREAKIN out. So I said, \"DON\'T WORRY, MOM, IT\'S NOT DEADLY!\" and she laughed. She whipped her wondow cleaner and fixed it. I was like what the crap we\'re not greek, and she said it had ammonia in it. So I thought okay whatever. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWell