ut it was dark. It was so cool. Like a tree top city with many lights. And a willow tree. It\'s basically just like Sharptop, but with a much smaller lake and much more hilly. That place is so pretty. I just loved the hills. Oh well enough of that. We went in the food place and got assigned (or volunteered) jobs. I was a server. Being a server was awesome. (Except for once, but that\'s a long story.) I got to talk to lots of people. Setting up and cleaning up sucked though. And vaqcuuming, ew I hated that. Ha, don\'t worry, I paid to work. We had a lot of fun. Taking out the trash was the most fun. And pouring the raging river of tea and put them on the tables. I got to play with the cart. It was Xtreme. Now I have lots of respect for people that work everyday. Especially waiters and waitresses. It was exhausting. We got a <i>lot</i> of freetime though. We also worked a <i>lot</i>. After we got assigned things, we set up for breakfast the next morning. I saw a girl working with us, but she wasn\'t from Sugarloaf. I saw her talkign to Jacob and when I walked over, Jacob told me she knew all of my friends and all of his friends. It was crazy. She knew Mary. And she said she knew Garrick. That\'s crazy. Her name was Megan. Jacob and I hung out with her some which was cool. Even though we worked a ton, it was so much fun. I didn\'t ride the zipline. What a shame. Jacob had an ear infection(which means he couldn\'t get in the water) and I was with him the whole time so I just never did it. Tait came. It was awesome to see him. The first night we played volleyball/soccer to the xtreme with a bunch of little kids the first night. We played Mafia in our cabin after that. It was fun the first time, but after that it was dumb. The next night I fell in the lake fully clothed which totally sucked. I had my camera and my brand new mp3 player in my pocket. I had my Five Iron Frenzy hoodie on, too. Both stopped working. They\'re okay now. I hope my jacket doesn;t shrink. The next 