 back out and yet again, they said they didn\'t ask for it. By now I was about to scream. I went back to get all the desert (that\'s 4 trips, but somehow, many had already gotten desert) and when I had finally finished I sat down. I was mad so I told everyone in the kitchen that coffee was stupid and should be different colors so that I wouldn\'t get them mixed up. That made me feel better. I was stressed out so I sat down outside the kitchen (in the room where eveyone was eating) and listened to Tait talk. Eventually, this lady that was all pissed off walked up to me and said, \"My husband and I still haven\'t gotten our coffee!\" I thought, \"You know what, screw you.\" I just went in the kitchen and stayed there. I might have tried to bring it out to them, but everyone was dismissed when I came out. Also, the next morning, Kelsey was being I want to cuss you out stupid. I can\'t stand that girl. Whatever happened to love your enemies. holy crap that\'s hard. Then we headed home and it took forever to get home. It was okay though. My mom was being I want to cuss you out stupid, too. We didn\'t have Bible Study.\r\n\r\nAs for today, it was pointless. I waited for the bus for 20 minutes and it never came, so we drove to school and then it came. I was listening to the radio and the guy said some school systems were canceled. I listened closely. Not ours. So, we went to school and it took forever because of flooding and traffic and such. The whole day, we didn\'t have any power except for a few lights here and there. No air conditioning.  In Latin, we just played Mafia because I had just learned how to play and told everyone. It was really stupid. No one could play it good. or well. whichever. Math was hot. On the way home, I was wondering if I had learned a single thing that day or not. All I could think of was that if there is a hurricane, they won\'t count you late if you get there at 7:30.\r\n\r\n\r\nEveryone thought I was acting weird yesterday. Sorry, I didn\'t 