17:12:00','2004-09-22 17:12:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=319',0,'post','',2),(320,2,'2004-09-23 18:35:00','2004-09-23 18:35:00','Russell Strauss\r\nSailors Gifted 9th grade LA\r\n22 September 2004\r\nPersuasive Essay\r\n\r\nMy parents are too strict about concerts. Do not get me wrong, I am extremely thankful that they allow me to go to concerts at all, but they should not let me go to certain concerts and not others (within reason). When I tell them about a concert that is more hardcore than others, they hesitate. Also, they have let me go to concerts on school nights before, but other times, will not let me. Normally, they drop me off, (granted that I have my friends or someone else to keep me safe) and go do other things around the city until it is time to go home. The time is up to their discretion. \r\n	One specific show that I want to go to is a band called Norma Jean. This is the kind of band that my parents say is loud and that you cannot understand. All of the music I listen to is positive and appropriate. Norma Jean is a band that reaches out to people that may shut their ears to what a church, friend, or leader might have to say to them. There are even things they say in their music and on and off stage the show that they are Christian and have good morals. When a girl at Cornerstone—a festival they played at—got hurt, they said on their website, “…and there was no physical damage or anything like that, which I guess means it was a spiritual happening. Something on a far deeper and more serious level than the physical level than the physical. This is about all that we know about it. We did not talk to the girl, but after the show, we, and some of our friends, spent a lot of time in prayer, which was a really good thing. Just praying for her and many other things in our lives. So, whatever it was, it led to much unity between us and our friends….and the body of Christ in general.” \r\nIn their music, they have things to say like, “Christ is not a fashion, fleeting away,” and “Stop searching and find Me, I am stabbed by grace and slinging blood,” referring to Jesus, and “God has stolen my heart, so I will write it down.” Though some of the lyrics are violent, it is because the world is such a violent place. It is not for just the reason of mindless violence that many movies, books, music, magazines, etc. of today present. They should be much more concerned with the movies I see or the things I see or read on the internet than my idea of what is an appropriate concert. They also don’t like how Norma Jean and many other bands scream, but there are many different kinds of music. Other types of music like opera, you cannot understand, but that does not mean that it is “demon possessed”. They tell me that they don’t listen to opera and that my music is “demon possessed”. When I talk to them about it not being demon possessed, they tell me that they are just kidding, but none of these bands even come close to this. They serve a complete opposite purpose. Screaming can be just as normal as whispering or singing softly, just on the opposite side or that scale. For example, Underoath screams, “Jesus, I’m ready to come home,” and New Day Awakening screams, “Holy, holy, holy, is the lamb. I bow my face before the King. This King is everything. You are my God. You are everything. And I worship you. I worship you Spirit of Truth. And I just lay my face upon the floor…” It can be just as emotional as singing quietly.\r\n	Also, they won’t let me go on school nights. Now this can be good because it’s not a good habit to do things far away on school nights, but I should be able to on occasions. Many bands only come around so often, and the chance of them coming on a Friday night is very small. Now on a school night, homework and sleep are very important. It shouldn’t be lost for a concert; it could even make grades drop. Though this is true, there are ways to avoid the consequences. You could get extra sleep the night before, and make sure all your homework is done before you leave. You could even take a nap before the show.\r\n	So though some of this music sounds like it is a bad type of music to listen to, there is nothing wrong with it. They are all Christian bands that have very good causes. I should be able to go to a Norma Jean concert just as much as I can any other concert.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure if it\'s good or not, but whether it\'s good or bad, I hope you like it. Now that I have this out of the way, I don\'t have much to worry about.','breathing out suicide','','publish','open','open','','breathing-out-suicide','','','2004-09-23 18:35:00','2004-09-23 18:35:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=320',0,'post','',8),(321,2,'2004-09-25 21:55:00','2004-09-25 21:55:00','I\'ve decided that curious is definitely my favorite icon.','They don\'t want the God. They don\'t want the life. They just want to put up a fight.','','publish','open','open','','they-dont-want-the-god-they-dont-want-the-life-they-just-want-to-put-up-a-fight','','','2004-09-25 21:55:00','2004-09-25 21:55:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=321',0,'post','',3),(322,2,'2004-09-26 16:55:00','2004-09-26 16:55:00','Look what today is.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n...I bet Chance knows.','365 days','','publish','open','open','','365-days','','','2004-09-26 16:55:00','2004-09-26 16:55:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=322',0,'post','',0),(323,2,'2004-09-26 22:50:00','2004-09-26 22:50:00','Russell Strauss\r\nSailors \r\nGifted 9th grade LA\r\n22 September 2004\r\n\r\nThe rules about concerts are too strict. Do not get me wrong, I am extremely thankful that you allow me to go to concerts at all, but you should not let me go to certain concerts and not others (within reason). When I tell you about a concert that is more hardcore than others, you hesitate. Also, you have let me go to concerts on school nights before, but other times, will not let me. Normally, you drop me off, (granted that I have my friends o