 know. Faith is \"don\'t let those pesky facts get in the way of our political plan or our mystically ordained path to heaven\"; faith is \"do what I tell you because I said so\". All things that can\'t be disproved need faith, utopia needs faith, idealism needs faith, spiritual salvation needs faith.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI went to a football game last night. It was my frist one except for NG homecoming last year. Actually, I remember going to a Brookwood game <i>years</i> ago. Chris, Heather, Chuck, Drew, Haley, and I went. Afterwards, we went to the place in downtown Dacula and the Melins played. It was awesome. I didn\'t love their music, but they were <i>extremely</i> talented. It was like ska without trumpets/rap/hardcore. The band wasn\'t really that hardcore, the setting just made them seem hardcore. They were awesome though. Yeah it was pretty awesome. Then Drew and Chuck came over. Yesterday after school, I went to Hebron to pick up Chuck and everyone was like AHH RUSSELL and it was so cool because I knew everyone. I wish I could go to that school so bad. I know it\'s not all fun and games like it seems though. I just seriously think if God wants me to go there then i will, so I don\'t have to worry about. I don\'t think he does but eh, who knows. At Bible Study every week, they always ask what God has been sayign to you and I never really know what to tell them but right now I know that I seriously need to watch what I say. At Altaer we talked about how the tongue can destroy anything or fix everything, at the Melin show they talked about the same thing in James, I\'ve noticed how extremely rude and mean everybody is to each other, I\'ve noticed how mean I am to other people, I remember when Dustin got mad at us at Bible Study for putting everyone down, and I\'ve just noticed how much it hurts. They may not even realize it. \r\n\r\nLast night was the coldest night of my life. I got to talk to Chris Cooley and he drew the most amazing picture in my journal. Garrick and Gee off stood us up for the Mill Creek game.\r\n\r\nAnyway, I am getting a Norma Jean hoodie. it\'s gonna be friggen sweet. Roepr cd comes out Tuesday. It\'s gonna be even friggen sweeter.\r\n\r\nThis weather is AMAZING.\r\n\r\n<font color=\"black\">I have toiled more years and never felt the cost,\r\nAnd I\'ve been burned by this world\'s cold like leaves beneath the frost.</font>','There is nothing more beautiful than a man after God\'s own heart.','','publish','open','open','pickle','there-is-nothing-more-beautiful-than-a-man-after-gods-own-heart','','','2004-10-16 14:42:00','2004-10-16 14:42:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=343',0,'post','',1),(344,2,'2004-10-17 00:03:00','2004-10-17 00:03:00','I\'m friggen tired. I\'m going to sleep.','shutup','','publish','open','open','','shutup','','','2004-10-17 00:03:00','2004-10-17 00:03:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=344',0,'post','',2),(345,2,'2004-10-17 13:20:00','2004-10-17 13:20:00','Nobody comments on my journals I feel like a loser.','','','publish','open','open','','345','','','2004-10-17 13:20:00','2004-10-17 13:20:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=345',0,'post','',14),(346,2,'2004-10-17 22:01:00','2004-10-17 22:01:00','Well I\'m too lazy to make a full entry as always, but some interesting things that have happened might defninitely not be:\r\n\r\n- Brad and I almost being victims of a drive by at Dacula Middle, main.\r\n- I went on a 20 mile bike ride all around Dacula. I went to the Ingles at the end of Dacula road, Drew\'s house, Chance\'s house, Hebron church, both Hebron schools, Downtown Dacula, Publix, and the such.\r\n- Going to the coldest football game ever.\r\n- and that\'s about it.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd we\'ll conclude with this:\r\n<table style=\'font-family : Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; border-collapse: collapse; border: 1px solid black;\' cellspacing=\'0\' cellpadding=\'2\' align=\'center\'><form action=\'http://memegen.net/viewmeme.pl?meme=1074647975\' meth