en','','583','','','2012-05-29 23:24:00','2012-05-29 23:24:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=583',0,'post','',0),(584,2,'2012-05-30 00:35:00','2012-05-30 00:35:00','I feel so many emotions. It&#39;s so hard to deal with so many emotions. I&#39;m so emotional, but there&#39;s nothing I can do about it. I feel so strongly, yet nothing I can do will calm them. They&#39;re passionate. They&#39;re angry. They&#39;re wonderful. They&#39;re terrible. They&#39;re so normal, but so misunderstood.\r\n\r\nIt&#39;s like I never learned to love. No one ever walked me through it. No one taught me how to do it. No one told me that it&#39;s real, and it&#39;s not enough to feel, it&#39;s not enough to promise, it&#39;s not enough to try.\r\n\r\nYou misunderstand them so terribly that I have no idea how to react. They&#39;re so right, yet you think they&#39;re so wrong. You think I&#39;m wrong. You think I&#39;m selfish, yet all I want is to make you happy.\r\n\r\nAll I want is to be happy. Maybe I&#39;ve spent so long putting off my own priorities, not being satisfied, that I&#39;m losing sight of what wanting to make you happy feels like. But I don&#39;t think that&#39;s true. That&#39;s the trap. It makes me so upset that you feel that way. No one has ever felt that way. Thinking about it just makes me hurt.\r\n\r\nI&#39;m sitting here late at night going through your stuff. I&#39;m just trying to make you happy. Yet you don&#39;t even make half the effort to make me happy. How could you call me selfish? I can&#39;t continue to think about it or I will begin to become selfish. I do my best to make you happy, but I can&#39;t do any better than my best. I think you will come around some day. I love you. It shows, but you can&#39;t see it. I hope that you will see it some day.\r\n\r\nIf you don&#39;t, I will continue. I&#39;m hardened and calloused, but that&#39;s what allows me to survive. It makes me dull. It might make me unpleasant, but it allows me to survive. Maybe if you can penetrate my shell, I&#39;ll know you&#39;re worth it.\r\n\r\nI&#39;m so hopeless for you, but so unconvinced. I&#39;m so torn. Everything in me says you&#39;re perfect, and that&#39;s exactly why I&#39;m not convinced. I will wait for you to tear my world apart to know for sure.\r\n\r\nI just wish you knew how much I&#39;m not satisfied. Then maybe you wouldn&#39;t call me selfish. Then maybe you wouldn&#39;t hurt me like you do.\r\n\r\nI get to the point that I have so many things pent up inside of me that I need to get out, but the more I try to let them out, the more distorted they get.\r\n\r\nNobody&#39;s free. Even the birds are chained to the sky.','','','publish','open','open','','584','','','2012-05-30 00:35:00','2012-05-30 00:35:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=584',0,'post','',1),(585,2,'2012-06-12 12:24:00','2012-06-12 12:24:00','Once in a while the cool breeze makes the summer seem cold.&nbsp;Once in a while you forget everything that your told.&nbsp;Spent the night without a cent to your name, everybody was happy you came, and youʼre gone.&nbsp;One more for the road.&nbsp;Once in a while her best dress looks tattered and torn.&nbsp;Sheʼs got an ace up her sleeve, blackjack, but sheʼs already won.&nbsp;She could never get to one million, so you tell her just to count to one, and youʼre gone.&nbsp;One more for the road.','','','publish','open','open','','585','','','2012-06-12 12:24:00','2012-06-12 12:24:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=585',0,'post','',0),(586,2,'2012-06-20 22:44:00','2012-06-20 22:44:00','I never chose between sides. I never chose between two. I just wanted you.','','','publish','open','open','','586','','','2012-06-20 22:44:00','2012-06-20 22:44:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=586',0,'post','',0),(587,2,'2012-06-26 23:18:00','2012-06-26 23:18:00','I&#39;m drinking by myself.','','','private','open','open','','587','','','2012-06-26 23:18:00','2012-06-26 23:18:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=587',0,'post','',0),(588,2,'2012-06-28 00:37:00','2012-06-28 00:37:00','I haven&#39;t used my computer in about a week. I had windows scattered all over the screen. I tried to quit all of the open programs and got an alert from TextEdit: &quot;Would you like to save this message?&quot;<br /><br />I looked on my screen and saw writing I did not recognize. I don&#39;t know who did this. But there it was. A message specifically written to me.<br /><br /><hr /><br />love is the best thing we can ever have.<br />love is also the worst thing that can destroy us.<br /><br />deep in our DNA we are programmed<br />not to kill ourselves.<br /><br /><br />or so i hear&hellip;<br /><br /><br />you deserve the best.<br />even if times you feel like the worst.<br /><br /><br />i don&#39;t know who you are, but i love you.<br /><br />if i could save a hug between<br />this computer screen and<br />the keyboard i would.<br /><br />i think we all wish we could<br />wake up to a message like this.<br /><br /><br /><br />that&#39;s why i wrote this for you.<br /><br /><i><b>you matter.</b></i>','','','publish','open','open','','588','','','2012-06-28 00:37:00','2012-06-28 00:37:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=588',0,'post','',0),(589,2,'2012-06-28 23:21:00','2012-06-28 23:21:00','I want to describe a time in my life that I will never forget. I should have done it long ago, while it was still fresh in my memory, but the longer I wait, the foggier it will get. Only months later, and it&#39;s already starting to fade. It&#39;s so sad, because they&#39;re some of the most precious memories I&#39;ve ever made in my entire life. I&#39;m so passionately dreading the day when I can&#39;t remember every little single detail of those three weeks of my life--and that is already starting to happen. I would give anything to have every moment perfectly documented out and preserved forever. So I must remember everything I can possibly remember before it fades away.<br /><br />On one Saturday night, 3 weeks before my college graduation--the last semester of my senior year of college, I went to a party at my good friend Lee&#39;s. It was April 14th, 2012. He had these parties often--probably once a month, and my best friend David and I had been frequenting them quite often that semester in particular. They weren&#39;t always packed, and they weren&#39;t always crazy, but sometimes they were, and they were most usually always fun. I got to see the circle of friends that would always be there, so I enjoyed going to see them and have a good time. This one in particular was one of the last. There weren&#39;t that many people there because they had just had one recently, but in the end, it was a solid group of people and everyone ended up having a wonderful time. There had been a girl I had somewhat expressed interest in, and I wanted to take her and show her how much fun my group of friends had when they party, yet I never expected I would meet someone that would completely change my life.&nbsp;<br /><br />I knew most everyone there. I met a couple new faces, and then had gotten acquainted with basically everyone at the party. I had a pretty big reputation among this group of friends, so it typically wasn&#39;t difficult to make friends with everyone there. Although, there were two girls whom I didn&#39;t recognize after I knew everyone, so I just decided to introduce myself.<br /><br />-&quot;Hey, I&#39;m Megan.&quot;&nbsp;<br />-&quot;And I&#39;m Clara.&quot;<br />-&quot;Clara?&quot;<br />-&quot;Yeah.&quot;<br />-&quot;Cool, hey.&quot;<br /><br />They&#39;re both very attractive young ladies, and they seemed to be having a very good time, but Clara was absolutely stunning. The longer I looked at her, the more beautiful I realized she was. I didn&#39;t talk to them really, but continued to mingle and have fun. Later in the night, Clara was nearby as I was talking to someone, and she grabbed my glasses and my hat off of me. It was my favorite hat of all time--the Cleveland Indians hat from my little league baseball team that I had from when I was a litte kid. I was&nbsp;desperately&nbsp;terrified of losing it whenever I took it out of the house. I thought about trying to grab it back, I might have even tried, but thought to myself, &quot;Well, I guess I&#39;m not getting that back right away. I&#39;ll get it back later.&quot; I thoroughly enjoyed the attention from her, so I was relaxed about it. I knew it would give me an excuse to talk to her later.&nbsp;<br /><br />Time passed, and I eventually went to the dance floor where I saw her, along with Megan and their friend William, dancing. Megan and William were dancing together. Clara had on the cutest red dress on, and I just couldn&#39;t get over how adorable she was. She was still wearing my hat and glasses. It was funny because she had probably had them on for at least 20 minutes, but I think it was even longer than that. I grabbed them back. She grabbed me and started dancing with me. I will never forget that moment because literally all I could think was, &quot;Is this really happening to me?&quot; That never happened with me. I never got to dance with girls, much less get grabbed by them. We held hands and danced for a long time. Neither of us were very drunk; I was sober enough for it to be self-conscious and awkward feeling, but I was still having a good time. I didn&#39;t ever want it to end. I felt weird about it because I had brought a different girl to the party to try and impress her, but in this moment, I really didn&#39;t care. I didn&#39;t expect it to go anywhere, but I was holding her hands and dancing with her--I never wanted it to end. Before a long time at all, Megan and William decided that it was time to leave. She told me she had to go. I was&nbsp;disappointed&nbsp;that she was leaving so soon, but there was nothing I could really do about it.<br /><br />&quot;Hey! This was fun! Will you find me on Facebook?&quot;&nbsp;She gave me the strangest look of disdain. I didn&#39;t understand it. But without hesitating for even half a second, I corrected myself: &quot;No! No! I&#39;ll find YOU! What&#39;s your last name?&quot;<br /><br />&quot;Gilbert.&quot;<br /><br />And then she left. I didn&#39;t really know what to do at this point. I continued to mingle with my friends and have fun, but was sad it had ended so soon. I didn&#39;t know if I would ever even see her again. I might have stayed another hour or two, then I went home. Berenice wasn&#39;t feeling good, but when she felt good enough to go, her, David, and I left to walk home. We got home and I tucked Berenice in and went to sleep in my own bed. All I could think about was Clara. I stayed up so long thinking about her that night. I had even friended her on Facebook before I got in bed. While lying in bed, I decided I would ask for her number the next day, call her up, and immediately ask her out for dinner for the following weekend. It was a Saturday night. I would typically never have the confidence to do something so suddenly, but I guess that&#39;s just the kind of thing love at first sight does to you.&nbsp;I also didn&#39;t have much time before summer came and everyone left. I had no idea if she would be here for the summer.<br /><br />I woke up the next morning and sent her a message:<br /><br /><div>-&quot;CLARA!&quot;</div><div>-&quot;RUSSELL!&quot;</div><div>-&quot;so i guess we are friends now...&quot;</div><div>-&quot;Of course we are! it was destiny.</div><div>clara, I had so much fun dancing with you last night. I want to hang out more.&quot;</div><div>-&quot;ok. done. i love adventures.&quot;</div><div>-&quot;HAHA.</div><div>perfect.</div><div>what&#39;s your phone number?&quot;</div><div>-&quot;478 251 1493</div><div>you are only slightly creepy by the way, but thats ok, because I think you are fun.&quot;</div><div>-&quot;haha what! why am I creepy??&quot;</div><div>-&quot;finding me and asking for my number...</div><div>its ok.&quot;</div><div>-&quot;you don&#39;t make friends with people after you meet them?&quot;</div><div>-&quot;you are probably looking at all my friends and pictures as we speak</div><div>.... hahaha&quot;<br /><br /><div>-&quot;what kind of adventure do you want to go on?&quot;</div><div>-&quot;well i have a feeling you are a pretty adventurous kid, so i am willing to let you make that call.&quot;<br /><br />Her calling me &quot;creepy&quot; robbed me of all the confidence I needed to call her up and ask her out right then and there. I sent her my number and a text or two, but was very conservative about it. Yet, the texts just continued back and forth; I didn&#39;t want to push it too hard. David and I were out shooting for our documentary, and Clara was in studio while we texted back in forth. Later, I got a text that made me terrified.&nbsp;<br /><br />-&quot;I need a break.&quot;<br />I hesitated then responded:<br />-&quot;From me sending you silly pictures?&quot;<br />-&quot;From studio.&quot;<br />My heart leapt, but I was still hesitant. I had only met her the night before. It was around 3 o&#39;clock.&nbsp;<br />-&quot;Did you want to meet up or do something?&quot;<br />-&quot;Sure, I&#39;m going to church with a friend in about 2 hours, but I have a little time to kill before then.&quot;<br /><br />Good news. She&#39;s a Christian. That&#39;s cool. I got excited.&nbsp;I called her to ask what we wanted to do. I told her we didn&#39;t have much time, but I could come pick her up and we could go cruising around for a little bit. After taking care of the camera equipment and taking my project team back to their cars, I left to go meet up with her. She sat in the grass outside of the architecture building waiting. I didn&#39;t really know what we could do, but I wasn&#39;t extremely concerned or nervous. But I was nervous. We started driving and I suggested I could take her to a cool antique store in the Highlands that David and I had found. We went and browsed for a little bit, but it was already time for her to go for church. She was meeting a friend, and we were already a little late. She invited me, and we decided to meet her friend, Michael Chaney, there. It was such a good sign to me. We went, and I felt good vibes from her. Honestly, there wasn&#39;t really a time that I didn&#39;t get good vibes from her from the second I met her, with the exception of her calling me creepy. After getting out, Michael suggested exactly what I was hoping, &quot;Are you guys hungry?&quot; Clara was. They wanted to go to the new dining hall, which I had never gotten to go to since I hadn&#39;t had a meal plan since I had been a freshman and wanted to try out before I graduated. It was the perfect opportunity! As the night went on, we all ate dinner together and sat talking for a long time. We finally walked out the door and sat outside, talking and enjoying the night. It wasn&#39;t until ten o&#39;clock that we decided to go. Michael went back into his apartment at North Ave, and Clara and I walked down Techwood together, in the direction of both my car and her dorm. She had left her bag in my car. She got her bag and we stood there for a couple minutes. I asked her what she was going to do that night. She told me that she had to do laundry, but she hated doing it alone and all of her friends were busy (we had seen them as we walked down Techwood). I wanted to tell her I would come so badly, but I didn&#39;t want to push it too hard. I had only met her last night. And even though I thought she wanted me to, I wanted to play my cards right. We just sat there in silence and looked at each other. She smiled at me with the most charming smile that could drive a guy wild. And it drove me wild. I smiled back. We looked at each other without saying anything. It should have been awkward, but it wasn&#39;t. I felt so natural with her. I said goodbye and left. I was so&nbsp;ecstatic about how glorious the day had been. I met up with her a little bit before 5 o&#39;clock to possibly hang out for an hour and we had spent the entire evening together. I couldn&#39;t stop smiling.&nbsp;<br /><br />She told me later that that moment was her favorite memory of us together: when we just looked at other smiling, not knowing what to do or say. She wanted to ask if I had any homework to do, if I wanted to come up to her room and study together. I would have said yes, but I suppose she was feeling the same way I was. I went home so happy and excited that night. I remember it vividly. I was already crazy about her.<br /><br />And after that, everything blurs together. It was a glorious three weeks, packed with time spent with her, school, graduation, finals, so much going on. I was living absolutely full speed. I&#39;m beginning to forget it all, but I would do anything to keep that from happening. It&#39;s all in my head, but I don&#39;t know how to extract it.<br /><br />The next day, I felt much better. I just couldn&#39;t believe how well things had gone that day. We continued talking, continued texting. We found excuses to hang out. She told me about her &quot;double lofted megabed&quot; and her room. I was curious. She asked me to come study with her. We decided to pick up some beer, and I came over. We spent the evening doing homework together.&nbsp;I had gone over later in the evening, maybe 7 o&#39;clock. She talked the night before about how she didn&#39;t like sleeping alone, that her room was great for slumber parties. We relaxed, enjoyed each other&#39;s company, and got to know each other.&nbsp;It was a lucky night for me in that I didn&#39;t have that much work to do. I drank a lot more than she did.&nbsp;It got dark. It was dim in her room. As we sat in her room alone, she wrote me a message on a sticky note and stuck it to me. She wanted to kiss me. We went back and forth a few times. Then I kissed her. We spent time enjoying the moment, enjoying each other, learning the taste of each other. We thought about how we had met 2 nights earlier. We were lying down, and she got tired. She wanted to go to sleep. We&nbsp;laid&nbsp;in her bed until she fell asleep. I gave myself time to lie there and sober up, then I quietly got out of bed, slipped out the door, and drove home.&nbsp;That was the last night I ever slept alone until I graduated, she left for the summer, and we were forced apart.&nbsp;</div><div><br />We did the same thing the next night, but this time I stayed. There wasn&#39;t really any question that I was going to. It was natural. From that day forward, we spent every second outside of class together. We ate lunch together, we ate dinner together, we spent time together every night, I went to visit her in studio, and I stayed with her every night.&nbsp;</div></div><br />','For my love, wherever I may find her','','private','open','open','','for-my-love-wherever-i-may-find-her','','','2012-06-28 23:21:00','2012-06-28 23:21:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=589',0,'post','',0),(590,2,'2012-07-10 14:13:00','2012-07-10 14:13:00','Russell Strauss: Can I invade your personal life and probe you for advice?\r\nMelissa Jackson: Sure! What&#39;s up?\r\nRussell: You&#39;re not a virgin, right?\r\nMelissa: Nope.&nbsp;\r\nRussell: Do you regret that?\r\nMelissa: I don&#39;t regret it. Like in the sense that I feel guilty. I think it may have been more special if I had waited for my wedding night. But I&#39;m perfectly happy with the fact that I did it when I did and with who I did.\r\nRussell: I thought you would say that. Do you think it has taken away from your life in any way whatsoever?\r\nMelissa: Yeah, I think a lot of people feel the same way. And it hasn&#39;t taken away from anything. It&#39;s added so much.&nbsp;\r\nRussell: Thanks, you&#39;re the best.\r\nMelissa: Anytime, duh.\r\nRussell: Do you think it&#39;s wrong?\r\nMelissa: I used to.&nbsp;\r\nRussell: It was the right decision?\r\nMelissa: No doubt.','','','private','open','open','','590','','','2012-07-10 14:13:00','2012-07-10 14:13:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=590',0,'post','',0),(591,2,'2012-07-10 16:15:00','2012-07-10 16:15:00','With the threat of hell hanging over my head like a halo,\r\nI was made to believe in a couple of beautiful truths,\r\nThat eventually had the effect of completely unraveling,\r\nThe powerful curse put on me by you.\r\n\r\nWhen you set the table,\r\nAnd when you chose the scale,\r\nDid you write a riddle,\r\nthat you knew they would fail?\r\n\r\nDid you make them tremble,\r\nso they would tell the tale?\r\nDid you push us when when we fell?\r\n\r\nIf my mother cries when I tell her what I have discovered,\r\nthen I hope she remembers she taught me to follow my heart.\r\nAnd if you bully her like you&#39;ve done me with fear of damnation,\r\nThen I hope she can see you for what you are.\r\n\r\nWhat am I afraid of?\r\nWhom did I betray?\r\nIn what medieval kingdom,\r\ndoes justice work this way?\r\n\r\nIf you knew what would happen,\r\nAnd made us just the same,\r\nThen you, my Lord, can take the blame.','when we fell','','publish','open','open','','when-we-fell','','','2012-07-10 16:15:00','2012-07-10 16:15:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=591',0,'post','',0),(592,2,'2012-07-10 20:53:00','2012-07-10 20:53:00','You’ve got to find the truth, and when you find that truth, you’ll find that that truth doesn’t budge, until the truth you’ve found begins to change. And it does. And when you love the truth enough, you start to tell it all the time, and when it gets you into trouble, you’ll discover you don’t mind.','','','publish','open','open','','592','','','2012-07-10 20:53:00','2012-07-10 20:53:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=592',0,'post','',0),(593,2,'2012-07-10 22:05:00','2012-07-10 22:05:00','I can\'t figure out if I\'m starting to believe want I want to believe, or what I truly believe.','','','publish','open','open','','593','','','2012-07-10 22:05:00','2012-07-10 22:05:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=593',0,'post','',0),(594,2,'2012-07-12 02:36:00','2012-07-12 02:36:00','I had the most wonderful weekend. Clara and I waited all summer to see each other. I finally got the chance to fly out and visit. I hadn&#39;t seen her for 8 weeks. I booked the flight about 4 weeks before the trip and the wait was killing us. But it finally came. It&#39;s finally come and gone, and that&#39;s weird to me. I was so outrageously anxious all summer long, and now it&#39;s over. But luckily, in the same way, she be back here before long. The end of the summer will come and go just in the same way. And that&#39;s what I tell myself. Time goes quickly when you only worry about today. Now that I&#39;m working, time flies by. It&#39;s strange.\r\n\r\nBut the time had finally come...thinking about it, I just can&#39;t get over the fact that it&#39;s over. It&#39;s so weird. It&#39;s like a dream. I guess that&#39;s why I want to preserve it forever right here. The time finally came and I made my journey to the airport. I was so excited. I couldn&#39;t contain myself. Many, many longs weeks, days, hours, and minutes of wait, but I finally landed in Minnesota. I walked outside, I was power walking, almost running, and looked for Clara. I didn&#39;t see her anywhere. It was intensely hot. I called her, but she didn&#39;t answer. I walked around for a minute, and then she called back. She was at baggage claim. I told her I was outside. I started walking inside but suddenly saw her coming up the escalator. I yelled at her to turn around and slammed up against the glass. We looked at each other, grinned ear to ear. I just sat there and she looked at me like, &quot;What are you crazy?? Get in here!!&quot; I sprinted inside and toward her. I tried to hug her, she tried to kiss me. It was awkward and funny. We kissed in the middle of the airport, so happy to be with each other, but we almost too excited to do so. We said hello and excitedly ran out the door. The ride home was lots of &quot;I can&#39;t believe you&#39;re here! I can&#39;t believe I&#39;m here!&quot; It was wonderful. We got to enjoy the hour long drive alone and take in what it was like to be together again.&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe had planned to go see a movie that night and were both excited about it. Clara was hungry, so she wanted to get home and change so we could go eat. We went by the grocery store on the way to pick up milk and ice cream. We went home changed, and finally left for the nearest movie theatre in a downtown square in a nearby town named Excelsior. We went to an italian restaurant in the square for dinner and had a wonderful, fancy, small, and expensive dinner with a bottle of wine. Before we left, she had said I could pick out her outfit. I told her that she couldn&#39;t just say no to whatever I picked, so I picked something. She looked at me, said &quot;Are you kidding me?&quot; and immediately said know. Because of that, I had been in a pretty bad mood the whole way there, so the wine helped with that and let me let go of it. We sat by the lake and then walked into the movie across the street. It was funny because we sat in the wrong theatre at first and didn&#39;t even realize it until the movei started. It was the tiniest little theatre, with only two movies playing. Our theatre only had five rows. Hilarious. It was a movie called Moonrise Kingdom. We enjoyed the movie then headed home. We were anxious to get on hands on each other, but couldn&#39;t do that at home. I wanted to more than she did. We talked about parking, but she didn&#39;t like the idea. She hadn&#39;t done it since high school. Neither had I. We parked and sat there for a second, but a car drove by, slowly, then slower, then slower, then stopped. So we started up the car and left. She wasn&#39;t willing to try anything else. I was mad.&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe went home with my irritation and I sat in her room alone. I told her I wanted to be alone. She said hello to her dad, but then eventually came in. She comforted me. I instantly knew everything was going to be alright. We had been struggling keeping each other happy all summer, but when we were together, all of that was gone. I had been terrified all summer that we would get back together and something would have changed since the previous semester. But it just reaffirmed everything that I had thought. We were both wonderful together, it was just the distance that was giving us so much trouble. Something about being apart just kept us from functioning. Yet, when we were together, all of that was gone. And in this moment, I was so satisfied to know that. So hopeful and optimistic. It was a big moment for me that confirmed that everything would be alright. We went on her porch and ate ice cream. It was a wonderful time. We sat and looked at each other and talked, comfortable. Her mom came in after a while, angry that she was eating after midnight, the night before the tests. We talked about what life was like in Minnesota and how much we missed each other. She cried and we held each other. It was so great to have each other to comfort. Before long, we decided to go to bed because we had to wake up early the next morning to go to the doctor to do some tests for her stomach issues, so we went to bed after that. We didn&#39;t get much sleep. I slept in her room, and she slept in her basement.\r\n\r\nWe woke up at 6:30. I was tired, but I felt alright. Just happy to be with Clara. She had gotten pretty upset earlier in the week when she found out she had to get up and go to the doctor to have some tests done during my visit. We got ready and headed to the hospital. She would have to eat radioactive eggs and get MRI&#39;s as they digested. She said that eggs usually made her feel bad and she didn&#39;t want to feel bad all day during our short time together, which is why she was upset about having to do the tests, along with having to wake up early. It took her a couple of hours, but her mom and I got some breakfast and coffee in the hospital cafe after a little bit. The bagel I ate was amazing. It was untoasted, but still so good. Just about the time we sat down, Clara came out of the tests. She had only been in there thirty or forty-five minutes, but she had to let the food digest before they took more pictures. Her coming out made all the difference. I thought I would have to sit alone with her mom all morning, but we got to stay together for the rest of the morning, mostly. She felt worse and worse the longer we stayed there. She got sick in the bathroom before we left, so I tried to comfort her there and on the way home. When we got home we took a nap in her room since we were both exhausted. I tried to fall asleep and came so frustratingly close, but then couldn&#39;t. The coffee I had was keeping me up. We eventually got up and found a note in the kitchen. The family had gone out to eat for lunch. We got alone time. We went back to bed and enjoyed the alone time. Though, her family came back before we were done and had to finish quickly.&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe had decided to go swimming that afternoon in a nearby lake. I wanted to go pick out a bathing suit since I hadn&#39;t owned one in years. We went by Kohl&#39;s and found some really great cheap bathing suits. I even found my favorite Adidas sandals on sale for an amazing price! I was so pumped about all of it. I got two great suits for twelve bucks each and the sandals for only twenty dollars. Super excited we headed off to the beach. Before that though, she took me to a tobacco shop in the nearby downtown area. It was the coolest tobacco shop I&#39;ve ever been in. They had so much pipe tobacco. I found this cool humidor that was cheap, so I decided to buy it. My dad had given me money for the trip and I emptied my entire high school change savings, so I had a little bit of money, which made the weekend so much better. We looked at the pipes. She found one she liked, but decided to wait to get it. As we left, we both could tell she really, really wanted it. It was a nice pipe for a decent price, and she seemed to be picky about them. Before we had gotten to the car, we laughed together and decided to go back and get it. It was so fun.&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe went to the beach and had a great time swimming. We just had a beautiful hour together, holding on to each other and enjoy our closeness and undivided attention. She was super into me at the moment. I loved it. We were happy. We got out after a while to lay on the beach before we left. There really isn&#39;t much to say except for how wonderful the time was together. We went home to make dinner. We made green bean casserole, bread, mashed potatoes, and salad. I had tried some anchovies at the italian restaurant the night before and loved them, so I was craving some more on my salad. We had stopped by the grocery store on the way home from the beach. After dinner, we relaxed and sat around for the evening. Star Wars was on TV, so we layed on the couch and watched it. After it ended, we watched American Pickers. I love that show. We began to dose off in each others arms. After a while, I realized I was asleep. I woke up and opened my eyes to see Clara, two inches from my face with my arms wrapped around her. I was absolutely overwhelmed with happiness. It was one of the most intense feelings I&#39;ve ever felt. I really don&#39;t know what is was, why I was feeling it, or where it came from. It was absolute bliss. I don&#39;t know how to explain it. I think part of it was being half asleep and just being wrapped into Clara. It felt so good. Since we were falling asleep, both of us were tired, we got up and headed off to our beds.&nbsp;','','','private','open','open','','594','','','2012-07-12 02:36:00','2012-07-12 02:36:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=594',0,'post','',0),(595,2,'2012-07-17 14:39:00','2012-07-17 14:39:00','I&#39;ve never been so torn between two things in my entire life. I can&#39;t handle this.&nbsp;','','','publish','open','open','','595','','','2012-07-17 14:39:00','2012-07-17 14:39:00','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=595',0,'post','',0),(651,2,'2012-08-27 23:40:52','2012-08-28 03:40:52','','to cyndi','','inherit','open','closed','','650-revision','','','2012-08-27 23:40:52','2012-08-28 03:40:52','',650,'http://journal.rruffles.com/650-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(599,2,'2012-07-24 23:35:57','2012-07-24 23:35:57','Something is right if nothing is right. We have a chemistry that can\'t exist without proximity.','us','','publish','open','closed','','us','','','2012-07-24 23:35:57','2012-07-24 23:35:57','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=599',0,'post','',0),(600,2,'2012-07-24 23:35:36','2012-07-24 23:35:36','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','closed','','599-revision','','','2012-07-24 23:35:36','2012-07-24 23:35:36','',599,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/599-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(601,2,'2012-07-26 01:09:26','2012-07-26 01:09:26','I believe that God gave me a brain for a reason. God gave me a heart to follow for a reason. He did not simply put me on this earth to follow rules, but to live life to its fullest.\r\n\r\nAnd life to its fullest means something different for every man. And that\'s why he gave me my head to use to my own advantage. I take what I learn from the Bible very liberally. I do not follow it word for word, nor do I agree with everything it says. Yet even then, I do not think it always leads me in the right direction when I follow it too strictly. There are too many contradictions to do so. God\'s word is not about rules, but about love. Do not misinterpret, I believe the word is a huge source of guidance that every man should look to for every decision he makes, but so many simply do not know how to read it. I\'m exaggerating a little and being a tad disrespectful, but trying to communicate my perspective without being able to easily do so. But what if God added these contradictions that we not listen to everything we are told but to learn from life and follow our hearts? I\'ve certainly learned that had I followed everything the church taught me and tried to live out the prude, closed-minded perspective of today\'s christians, I would not be living life to its fullest. I would be living a life that, to me, could not be its happiest.\r\n\r\nBut I\'ve carefully listened for God. I\'ve squinted my eyes, tried hard to see what\'s right, and attempted to follow after that small speck of light. I\'ve always done my best. And that\'s why I\'m completely happy. That\'s why I\'m completely satisfied with my life and where I am. But what if I don\'t continue to do this in everything that I do?\r\n\r\nI think I\'m coming to a fork in the road. I can decide to learn for myself and do as God has taught me, to follow my heart and take risks, or I can decide to live a sterile and protected life, free of potential hurt, missing out on things I need.\r\n\r\nBut am I just trying to justify a wrong decision? Possibly. Is it likely? Yes. But am I following my heart? Yes. Am I listening to everything that whispers guidance in my direction, trying desperately to figure out what is right? Of course I am.\r\n\r\nI may not make the right decision, but I will certainly make the decision that I believe is right, closely trying to live my life as God has taught me in order to live my life to its fullest potential.\r\n\r\nFollowing my heart one-hundred percent of the way.','the way i was made','','publish','open','closed','','the-way-i-was-made','','','2012-08-15 01:30:06','2012-08-15 06:30:06','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/journal/?p=601',0,'post','',0),(602,2,'2012-07-26 00:55:34','2012-07-26 00:55:34','I believe that God gave me a brain for a reason. God gave me a heart to follow for a reason. He did not simpy put me on this earth to follow rules, but to live life to its fullest.','the way i was made','','inherit','open','closed','','601-revision','','','2012-07-26 00:55:34','2012-07-26 00:55:34','',601,'http://jrstr