nd caring to me. You had a lot of sense and understanding and probably handled our situation exactly as it should have been handled, which is probably not true of my behavior from my end. It\'s been too long for me to truly know for sure, but of what little evidence I have of the communication between you and me, what I\'ve seen doesn\'t look like I treated you reasonably. That\'s not to say that I truly mistreated you--I don\'t think that is true--but I think that I could have been better. Well, I couldn\'t have been better, but I should have been. Had I known any better,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI\'ve learned a lot about myself in the past 6 years, and I can tell you that any way I treated you was not because I was a mean person or that I had bad intentions, but because I cared about you so much and wanted you in my life so badly that I eventually got to the point of desperation which completely distorts our own perception of how to act and how to not act. Regardless of how I acted or you acted or who was right and who was wrong, none of which I remember well enough to know either way, I want to extend an apology to you for anything in between--for what I did, for what I didn\'t do, for what I shouldn\'t have done, and for what I didn\'t know to do. I\'m making these judgements based on the fact that you haven\'t talked to me since, and clearly had no desire to do so many years ago. I can\'t do much, but I can tell you I\'m sorry. Even if I never was before, I am now.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI was always confused as to why you wouldn\'t talk to me. I\'m sure there was reason for a while, but I had hoped and expected that some time it would fade away and at least move in the positive direction, if only slightly, yet it only continued to move in the negative. For a long time, I did what I needed to do to rid myself of any attraction to you, which took many years, believe it or not, and I presume that is what caused so much harm, of all the things we ever went though. I want you to know that I feel no feelings of negativity to you in any way, regardless of what that might mean to you. I have many negative memories of us and feelings of hopelessness, but I\'ve shelved them away and dusted off the positive over the years and moved them to the front. I still remember what it was like the first day I met you and the power you had over me and my heart. I was such a helpless young man, and such a slave to my feelings. I still am really. You were so beautiful then, and I believe that if I knew you today, you still would be. Both inside your heart and outside in your presence.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI really, really hope that you are doing well. I really, really hope that you are happy. I hope that Boston was everything you ever dreamed it was and I hope that you\'ve found a happy life in what it\'s been after you knew me. You don\'t ever have to want to talk to me again, and that\'s perfectly okay, but I want to offer you a hand as a lost friend and any other benevolence that I can offer. I am still the exact same boy that you once knew and though I haven\'t changed much, I have certainly grown. And you were a huge part of that. And you gave me years and years of growth, even after I never knew you any more. There was a time in my life, long after you kindly let me out of your life that I didn\'t think I would ever stop struggling with the hole you left in it. And I was always surprised with how that was--I\'m sure I took things way too seriously. But it was mostly for how badly I wanted you and my life, yet that\'s just not how it works. Thank you for treating me how you did. Thank you for pushing me away when you realized you weren\'t happy. Thank you for being down to earth, blunt, and honest. Thank you for standing up for yourself. And most of all, thank you for not putting up with my emotions of desperation. Honestly, you probably put up with them much more than you should have.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI don\'t expect a response, and you certainly don\'t have to, but if it means anything to you and you would like to, I am completely open to hearing from you. Whether it\'s short, long, criticism, openness, small talk, an update, or a giant list of all the things you hated about me--I don\'t care--I will be open to anything and would love to hear from you regardless of what the content is. And if you\'re curious at all as to what my life is like or who I am these days, I will gladly tell you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf anything, I hope this letter is one of encouragement to you. You were such a light in my life and and though you were a very painful light, you taught me a lot and made me feel things I\'ve never felt before. You made me happier than anyone I had ever known. I still remember the feelings you made me feel that were unique in a way that no one has ever made me feel since--because you are your very own unique person that is different from anyone else. If I never hear from you again, I wish you the very best and hope that your life is a wonderful adventure full of twists, turns, surprises, and excitement.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLove from your old friend,\r\n\r\nRussell Strauss','to cyndi','','inherit','open','closed','','650-revision-2','','','2012-08-27 23:40:56','2012-08-28 03:40:56','',650,'http://journal.rruffles.com/650-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(653,2,'2012-08-27 23:56:55','2012-08-28 03:56:55','Dear Cyndi,\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI hope this letter brings you in good faith, good fortune, and times of happiness. I know you might not ever want to hear from me again, but I will give you the benefit of the doubt in the case that it will settle curiosity, peace of mind, or in the very least, interest. Today I was going through a box of old letters and read a few from you, still as crisp and neat as the day I got them. You were sweet to me, open, and understanding. I have a couple memories otherwise, but I think they are merely distortions of my perception at the time due to my hypersensi