 have.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI don\'t expect a response, and you certainly don\'t have to, but if it means anything to you and you would like to, I am completely open to hearing from you. Whether it\'s short, long, criticism, openness, small talk, an update, or a giant list of all the things you hated about me--I don\'t care--I will be open to anything and would love to hear from you regardless of what the content is. And if you\'re curious at all as to what my life is like or who I am these days, I will gladly tell you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf anything, I hope this letter is one of encouragement to you. You were such a light in my life and and though you were a very painful light, you taught me a lot and made me feel things I\'ve never felt before. You made me happier than anyone I had ever known. I still remember the feelings you made me feel that were unique in a way that no one has ever made me feel since--because you are your very own unique person that is different from anyone else. If I never hear from you again, I wish you the very best and hope that your life is a wonderful adventure full of twists, turns, surprises, and excitement.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nLove from your old friend,\n\nRussell Strauss','to cyndi','','inherit','open','closed','','650-autosave','','','2012-08-27 23:56:55','2012-08-28 03:56:55','',650,'http://journal.rruffles.com/650-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(654,2,'2012-08-28 14:57:13','2012-08-28 18:57:13','There is a time in every man\'s education when he arrives at the conviction that envy is ignorance; that imitation is suicide; that he must take himself for better, for worse, as his portion; that though the wide universe is full of good, no kernel of nourishing corn can come to him but through his toil bestowed on that plot of ground which is given to him to till...Whoso would be a man must be a nonconformist. He who would gather immortal palms must not be hindered by the name of goodness, but must explore if it be goodness. Nothing is at last sacred but the integrity of your own mind. Absolve you to yourself, and you shall have the suffrage of the world.','self-reliance','','publish','open','closed','','self-reliance','','','2012-10-01 22:06:36','2012-10-02 02:06:36','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=654',0,'post','',0),(655,2,'2012-08-28 14:56:52','2012-08-28 18:56:52','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','closed','','654-revision','','','2012-08-28 14:56:52','2012-08-28 18:56:52','',654,'http://journal.rruffles.com/654-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(656,2,'2012-08-28 14:57:13','2012-08-28 18:57:13','\"There is a time in every man\'s education when he arrives at the conviction that envy is ignorance; that imitation is suicide; that he must take himself for better, for worse, as his portion; that though the wide universe is full of good, no kernel of nourishing corn can come to him but through his toil bestowed on that plot of ground which is given to him to till...Whoso would be a man must be a nonconformist. He who would gather immortal palms must not be hindered by the name of goodness, but must explore if it be goodness. Nothing is at last sacred but the integrity of your own mind. Absolve you to yourself, and you shall have the suffrage of the world.\"','self-reliance','','inherit','open','closed','','654-revision-2','','','2012-08-28 14:57:13','2012-08-28 18:57:13','',654,'http://journal.rruffles.com/654-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(657,2,'2012-08-29 16:06:14','2012-08-29 20:06:14','I\'m so desperate. I\'m so miserable. I\'m so in need of love in a time completely void of love.','','','publish','open','closed','','a-time-void-of-love','','','2012-10-01 22:05:57','2012-10-02 02:05:57','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=657',0,'post','',0),(658,2,'2012-08-29 15:56:44','2012-08-29 19:56:44','I\'m so desperate. I\'m so miserable. I\'m so in need of love in a time completely void of love.','','','inherit','open','closed','','657-revision','','','2012-08-29 15:56:44','2012-08-29 19:56:44','',657,'http: