></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>fear<br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>pain<br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>loneliness<br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>desolation.<br><br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>Then<br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>I cry<br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>until I am<br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>too numbed<br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>to feel.<br><br></i></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><i>Interesting pastime.</i><br></div>','pastime','','publish','open','closed','','pastime','','','2012-10-23 16:26:03','2012-10-23 20:26:03','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=699',0,'post','',0),(682,2,'2012-10-01 21:39:24','2012-10-02 01:39:24','The way you treat me is completely unfair. In fact, everything you do to me is unfair. You apply such an extreme double standard that I have never experienced with anyone I\'ve ever known. And the worst part is that you get away with it. I will always fight to be the better person. I will always offer the treatment that I wish I could receive from you. Though I am doubtful, I pray that it will one day pay off.\r\n\r\nWhen I was younger, I wished to be like my mother. She is a bottomless fountain of mercy. She is a bottomless fountain of wisdom. After growing up with her in the family, taking care and neutralizing every single emotional crisis and conflict, it was something I could not miss. I was amazed by her ability to put her own needs so far behind her and give them away to us. It was a bittersweet desire. I admired the ability, yet I did not want the responsibility of learning how to live without having my needs met, shoving everything to the back to make room for my family\'s well-being. Though I didn\'t worry about this bittersweet desire, for I didn\'t believe I was like that. I didn\'t believe it was an ability I possessed. I believed it w