ision/',0,'revision','',0),(756,2,'2013-03-29 12:27:29','2013-03-29 16:27:29','The process of hiring &amp; employing is a two way street. If a company wants to hire you at $100,000, definitely they are planning to profit more than 100K themselves, probably much more. Otherwise they won\'t hire you. Companies are not in business for some other worldly altruistic cause, they want to make lots of profit out of your labor. So, they very much want to hire you. In fact they are desperate. E.g. Facebook &amp; Google competition.\r\n\r\nThe paradox is, even when the company\'s want/need for you is desperately crazy, they try to hide it in the \'people market\'. In fact they behave as if they really don\'t need you, as if they are doing you some extra-ordinary favor by employing you. In fact what they are actually doing in this \'trade negotiation\', is trying to downgrade your value, at the beginning of negotiations. They imply that you need them more than they need you. All their tactics of recruiting are geared toward this.\r\n\r\nTo counter this, first, you need to aware of it &amp; second, join together with other top people in an online group, where you discuss employers. Discuss the whole process of recruiting &amp; whether it is fair &amp; equal.\r\n\r\nStart from discussion of the advertisement itself. E.g if they want to know your salary right at the start, should they not include it in their ad, then give at least give a reasonably narrow salary range budgeted for that position. That would be equal &amp; fair. In some countries that actually is the standard practice.\r\n\r\nPractices we take for granted as \'unchangeable\' do get changed. E.g. in SV, the VC community has recently realized this (the two way traffic) when the entrepreneurs decided that not taking investor money is actually better in for them.\r\n\r\nIf the recruiters are \'partnering\' with the company, is it not their professional duty to inform their client company about this two way street &amp; refuse to deal with companies who insist on being unprofessional?','','','publish','open','closed','','756','','','2017-04-20 16:19:04','2017-04-20 20:19:04','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=756',0,'post','',0),(758,2,'2013-04-10 10:58:48','2013-04-10 14:58:48','Maybe I don\'t really want to know how your garden grows. I just want to fly. Lately have you felt the pain in the morning rain as it soaks it to the bone?\r\n\r\nMaybe I just want to fly. I want to live; I don\'t want to die. Maybe I just want to breath. Maybe I just don\'t believe. Maybe you\'re the same as me. We see things they\'ll never see. You and I are going to live forever.\r\n\r\nMaybe I will never be all the things that I want to be. But now is not the time to cry. Now\'s the time to find out why. I think you\'re the same as me. We see things they\'ll never see. You and I are going to live forever.','You and I are going to live forever.','','publish','open','closed','','you-and-i-are-going-to-live-forever','','','2013-04-10 10:58:48','2013-04-10 14:58:48','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=758',0,'post','',0),(759,2,'2013-04-10 10:58:25','2013-04-10 14:58:25','Maybe I don\'t really want to know how your garden grows. I just want to fly. Lately have you felt the pain in the morning rain as it soaks it to the bone?\n\nMaybe I just want to fly. I want to live; I don\'t want to die. Maybe I just want to breath. Maybe I just don\'t believe. Maybe you\'re the same as me. We see things they\'ll never see. You and I are going to live forever.\n\nMaybe I will never be all the things that I want to be. But now is not the time to cry. Now\'s the time to find out why. I think you\'re the same as me\nWe see things they\'ll never see\nYou and I are gonna live forever\nWe\'re gonna live forever\n\nGonna live forever\nLive forever\nForever','You and I are going to live forever.','','inherit','open','closed','','758-revision','','','2013-04-10 10:58:25','2013-04-10 14:58:25','',758,'http://journal.rruffles.com/758-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(841,2,'2015-12-19 10:46:05','2015-12-19 15:46:05','I had the most wonderful weekend. Clara and I waited all summer to see each other. I finally got the chance to fly out and visit. I hadn\'t seen her for 8 weeks. I booked the flight about 4 weeks before the trip and the wait was killing us. But it finally came. It\'s finally come and gone, and that\'s weird to me. I was so outrageously anxious all summer long, and now it\'s over. But luckily, in the same way, she be back here before long. The end of the summer will come and go just in the same way. And that\'s what I tell myself. Time goes quickly when you only worry about today. Now that I\'m working, time flies by. It\'s strange.\n\nBut the time had finally come...thinking about it, I just can\'t get over the fact that it\'s over. It\'s so weird. It\'s like a dream. I guess that\'s why I want to preserve it forever right here. The time finally came and I made my journey to the airport. I was so excited. I couldn\'t contain myself. Many, many longs weeks, days, hours, and minutes of wait, but I finally landed in Minnesota. I walked outside, I was power walking, almost running, and looked for Clara. I didn\'t see her anywhere. It was intensely hot. I called her, but she didn\'t answer. I walked around for a minute, and then she called back. She was at baggage claim. I told her I was outside. I started walking inside but suddenly saw her coming up the escalator. I yelled at her to turn around and slammed up against the glass. We looked at each other, grinned ear to ear. I just sat there and she looked at me like, \"What are you crazy?? Get in here!!\" I sprinted inside and toward her. I tried to hug her, she tried to kiss me. It was awkward and funny. We kissed in the middle of the airport, so happy to be with each other, but we almost too excited to do so. We said hello and excitedly ran out the door. The ride home was lots of \"I can\'t believe you\'re here! I can\'t believe I\'m here!\" It was wonderful. We got to enjoy the hour long drive alone and take in what it was like to be together again.\n\nWe had planned to go see a movie that night and were both excited about it. Clara was hungry, so she wanted to get home and change so we could go eat. We went by the grocery store on the way to pick up milk and ice cream. We went home changed, and finally left for the nearest movie theatre in a downtown square in a nearby town named Excelsior. We went to an italian restaurant in the square for dinner and had a wonderful, fancy, small, and expensive dinner with a bottle of wine. Before we left, she had said I could pick out her outfit. I told her that she couldn\'t just say no to whatever I picked, so I picked something. She looked at me, said \"Are you kidding me?\" and immediately said know. Because of that, I had been in a pretty bad mood the whole way there, so the wine helped with that and let me let go of it. We sat by the lake and then walked into the movie across the street. It was funny because we sat in the wrong theatre at first and didn\'t even realize it until the movei started. It was the tiniest little theatre, with only two movies playing. Our theatre only had five rows. Hilarious. It was a movie called Moonrise Kingdom. We enjoyed the movie then headed home. We were anxious to get on hands on each other, but couldn\'t do that at home. I wanted to more than she did. We talked about parking, but she didn\'t like the idea. She hadn\'t done it since high school. Neither had I. We parked and sat there for a second, but a car drove by, slowly, then slower, then slower, then stopped. So we started up the car and left. She wasn\'t willing to try anything else. I was mad.\n\nWe went home with my irritation and I sat in her room alone. I told her I wanted to be alone. She said hello to her dad, but then eventually came in. She comforted me. I instantly knew everything was going to be alright. We had been struggling keeping each other happy all summer, but when we were together, all of that was gone. I had been terrified all summer that we would get back together and something would have changed since the previous semester. But it just reaffirmed everything that I had thought. We were both wonderful together, it was just the distance that was giving us so much trouble. Something about being apart just kept us from functioning. Yet, when we were together, all of that was gone. And in this moment, I was so satisfied to know that. So hopeful and optimistic. It was a big moment for me that confirmed that everything would be alright. We went on her porch and ate ice cream. It was a wonderful time. We sat and looked at each other and talked, comfortable. Her mom came in after a while, angry that she was eating after midnight, the night before the tests. We talked about what life was like in Minnesota and how much we missed each other. She cried and we held each other. It was so great to have each other to comfort. Before long, we decided to go to bed because we had to wake up early the next morning to go to the doctor to do some tests for her stomach issues, so we went to bed after that. We didn\'t get much sleep. I slept in her room, and she slept in her basement.\n\nWe woke up at 6:30. I was tired, but I felt alright. Just happy to be with Clara. She had gotten pretty upset earlier in the week when she found out she had to get up and go to the doctor to have some tests done during my visit. We got ready and headed to the hospital. She would have to eat radioactive eggs and get MRI\'s as they digested. She said that eggs usually made her feel bad and she didn\'t want to feel bad all day during our short time together, which is why she was upset about having to do the tests, along with having to wake up early. It took her a couple of hours, but her mom and I got some breakfast and coffee in the hospital cafe after a little bit. The bagel I ate was amazing. It was untoasted, but still so good. Just about the time we sat down, Clara came out of the tests. She had only been in there thirty or forty-five minutes, but she had to let the food digest before they took more pictures. Her coming out made all the difference. I thought I would have to sit alone with her mom all morning, but we got to stay together for the rest of the morning, mostly. She felt worse and worse the longer we stayed there. She got sick in the bathroom before we left, so I tried to comfort her there and on the way home. When we got home we took a nap in her room since we were both exhausted. I tried to fall asleep and came so frustratingly close, but then couldn\'t. The coffee I had was keeping me up. We eventually got up and found a note in the kitchen. The family had gone out to eat for lunch. We got alone time. We went back to bed and enjoyed the alone time. Though, her family came back before we were done and had to finish quickly.\n\nWe had decided to go swimming that afternoon in a nearby lake. I wanted to go pick out a bathing suit since I hadn\'t owned one in years. We went by Kohl\'s and found some really great cheap bathing suits. I even found my favorite Adidas sandals on sale for an amazing price! I was so pumped about all of it. I got two great suits for twelve bucks each and the sandals for only twenty dollars. Super excited we headed off to the beach. Before that though, she took me to a tobacco shop in the nearby downtown area. It was the coolest tobacco shop I\'ve ever been in. They had so much pipe tobacco. I found this cool humidor that was cheap, so I decided to buy it. My dad had given me money for the trip and I emptied my entire high school change savings, so I had a little bit of money, which made the weekend so much better. We looked at the pipes. She found one she liked, but decided to wait to get it. As we left, we both could tell she really, really wanted it. It was a nice pipe for a decent price, and she seemed to be picky about them. Before we had gotten to the car, we laughed together and decided to go back and get it. It was so fun.\n\nWe went to the beach and had a great time swimming. We just had a beautiful hour together, holding on to each other and enjoy our closeness and undivided attention. She was super into me at the moment. I loved it. We were happy. We got out after a while to lay on the beach before we left. There really isn\'t much to say except for how wonderful the time was together. We went home to make dinner. We made green bean casserole, bread, mashed potatoes, and salad. I had tried some anchovies at the italian restaurant the night before and loved them, so I was craving some more on my salad. We had stopped by the grocery store on the way home from the beach. After dinner, we relaxed and sat around for the evening. Star Wars was on TV, so we layed on the couch and watched it. After it ended, we watched American Pickers. I love that show. We began to dose off in each others arms. After a while, I realized I was asleep. I woke up and opened my eyes to see Clara, two inches from my face with my arms wrapped around her. I was absolutely overwhelmed with happiness. It was one of the most intense feelings I\'ve ever felt. I really don\'t know what is was, why I was feeling it, or where it came from. It was absolute bliss. I don\'t know how to explain it. I think part of it was being half asleep and just being wrapped into Clara. It felt so good. Since we were falling asleep, both of us were tired, we got up and headed off to our beds.','','','inherit','open','closed','','594-autosave-v1','','','2015-12-19 10:46:05','2015-12-19 15:46:05','',594,'http://journal.rruffles.com/594-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(762,2,'2013-04-29 00:33:07','2013-04-29 04:33:07','5. Megan Evans.\r\n04.29.2013.','Megan Evans','','private','open','closed','','762','','','2017-02-20 12:39:46','2017-02-20 17:39:46','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=762',0,'post','',0),(763,2,'2013-04-29 00:32:37','2013-04-29 04:32:37','3. Megan Evans.