ite is stored. Three weeks later, you finally have what you need to fix the stupid issue. And all the while, I get frustrated that I can\'t do anything, or if I can, that I don\'t know how to do it. But I am finally getting better at not getting caught up on every snag possible. I still have all these problems and many more, but after finishing my hike, I feel so much more at peace with the choice I made. I may not be one of the strongest</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Take on a writing challenge. Write something everyday for a month. Write something every week for 3 months.</li>\r\n 	<li>smoke less</li>\r\n 	<li>Catch, dress, cook, and eat 1 fish.</li>\r\n</ol>','New Year\'s Resolution 2017','','draft','open','closed','','','','','2017-01-06 14:09:55','2017-01-06 19:09:55','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=856',0,'post','',0),(857,2,'2017-01-05 15:11:55','2017-01-05 20:11:55','<ol>\r\n 	<li>Make something I\'m proud of.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>I\'m finally becoming much more satisfied with my career in web development because I\'m realizing that it is becoming more powerful and diverse than I ever thought it would. I wasn\'t satisfied with all of the difficulties of sitting at a computer all day, every day and struggling to understand how to perform well with the tasks that were assigned to me. I hated how much time is wasted trying to force square pegs into round holes or how to even find the square pegs, when I could be using my tie to actually create things that are interesting and valuable. I wasted so much time trying to do gymnastics to solve a problem when I just want to be creating something. And then once I became better at solving these problems, I have to deal with the politics of web development. You can\'t perform a simple task until you get approval from three separate entities that know nothing about how the task should be performed. And once you do, you have to send 50 emails trying to get the server information to where the web site is stored. Three w