tick of incredibly potent oregano. I had never had oregano so potent, and I wanted to know how he made it so potent. I kept it alive for a while and then forgot to water it for just a few days, not long at all, and it started dying. It had gotten cold, too, so I thought that could have caused it. But I cut the dead stuff and later it grew new leaves. I spent tons of time in the spring cutting the tips off, and now it is doing great. Now that it is finally outside it is starting to get full. I am very excited to see how much it grows this summer.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190736.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190736\" />\r\n\r\nHere you can see some other oreganos I bought. The back one is Hot and Spicy Oregano and it is just about as spicy as a pepper. Very intense but awesome. Syrian oregano in the front that will hopefully grow very big. The pitcher plant shot up as soon as I put it in the moss, growing 4 inches or more overnight and then growing at an amazing rate over 2-3 weeks. Now it looks amazing.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190728.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190728\" />\r\n\r\nBeautiful color.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190645.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190645\" />\r\n\r\nDana\'s Delight, just repotted.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190635.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190635\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191227.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191227\" />\r\n\r\nThe banana tree. It has not grown much at all. It just sprouted three leaves so hopefully it will start soon now that it\'s getting hot.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191222.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191222\" />\r\n\r\nPurple tomatillos. Sound awesome.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191214.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191214\" />\r\n\r\nCucumbers, okra, tomatoes, beets, onions, sunflowers. Pretty boring so far.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191211.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191211\" />\r\n\r\nThe cherry tomato is starting to finally do something.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191157.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191157\" />\r\n\r\nA ton of arugula and radishes.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191148.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191148\" />\r\n\r\nPeanuts!! Pumped about this one.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191128.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191128\" />\r\n\r\nLemon balm, some gnarled parsley, and something called lovage. Whatever that means. Tastes like potent celery. I like it.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191116.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191116\" />\r\n\r\nSome amazing types of peppers that haven\'t done anything exciting yet, but I know are definitely going to. There will be so many colors.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191106.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191106\" />\r\n\r\nBronze fennel. I ike to eat it a lot so I hope it grows.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191058.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191058\" />\r\n\r\nSome half dying basils in the back, cantaloupe, golden oregano, golden thyme, red sorrel. The sorrel has been growing great.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191049.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191049\" />\r\n\r\nItalian large leaf, one stalk survived. Thai is rocking, not as much as the one in the pot though. The boxwood basil died in the ground, too, but is killin it in the pot, so maybe it is shaded too much by the wall, but I don\'t know. I pruned it after transplanted and I think that killed the large leaf.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191043.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191043\" />\r\n\r\nCantaloupe starting to grow a little bit.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191010.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191010\" />\r\n\r\nParsley I am excited to eat. It is doing well. Hurry!!\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190943.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190943\" />\r\n\r\nPapalo! A taste of lime and cilantro. Very good. Now get big and strong!\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190938.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190938\" />\r\n\r\nPeruvian Black Mint. Very cool.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190931.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190931\" />\r\n\r\nSome Munstead Lavender.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190916.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190916\" />\r\n\r\nMint. It got dry and a bunch of leaves died. Now it has been watered but still looks bad compared to how I got it.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190908.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190908\" />\r\n\r\nRed sorrel looking great.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190856.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190856\" />\r\n\r\nZaatar which I found out is just oregano.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190850.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190850\" />\r\n\r\nSilver thyme. Really cool and smells good. The lemon balm in the back took forever to germinate and grow from seed. I think it needed warm weather.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190842.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190842\" />\r\n\r\nLavender.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190840.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190840\" />\r\n\r\nRosemary, super chill.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190823.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190823\" />\r\n\r\nThai basil. This one is doing awesome.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190818.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190818\" />\r\n\r\nShiso. Big already.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190808.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190808\" />\r\n\r\nVarious seedlings.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190800.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190800\" />\r\n\r\nTaters.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190750.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190750\" />\r\n\r\nHot and spicy again!\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190741.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190741\" />\r\n\r\nSyrian again, majectic.','Garden Inauguration 2017','','publish','open','closed','','garden-inauguration-2017','','','2017-04-26 13:55:52','2017-04-26 17:55:52','',0,'http://journal.rruffles.com/?p=1008',0,'post','',0),(1010,2,'2017-04-26 00:42:43','2017-04-26 04:42:43','<img src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190625.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190625\" />\r\n\r\nThis is the plant that started it all. Winston gave it to me, and it was just a very stiff stick of incredibly potent oregano. I had never had oregano so potent, and I wanted to know how he made it so potent. I kept it alive for a while and then forgot to water it for just a few days, not long at all, and it started dying. It had gotten cold, too, so I thought that could have caused it. But I cut the dead stuff and later it grew new leaves. I spent tons of time in the spring cutting the tips off, and now it is doing great. Now that it is finally outside it is starting to get full. I am very excited to see how much it grows this summer.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://journa