n amazing rate over 2-3 weeks. Now it looks amazing.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1006\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190728.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190728\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nBeautiful color.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1005\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190645.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190645\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nDana\'s Delight, just repotted.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1004\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190635.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190635\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1002\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191227.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191227\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nThe banana tree. It has not grown much at all. It just sprouted three leaves so hopefully it will start soon now that it\'s getting hot.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1001\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191222.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191222\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nPurple tomatillos. Sound awesome.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1000\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191214.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191214\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nCucumbers, okra, tomatoes, beets, onions, sunflowers. Pretty boring so far.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-999\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191211.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191211\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nThe cherry tomato is starting to finally do something.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-998\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191157.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191157\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nA ton of arugula and radishes.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-997\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191148.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191148\" />\r\n\r\nPeanuts!! Pumped about this one.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-996\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191128.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191128\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nLemon balm, some gnarled parsley, and something called lovage. Whatever that means. Tastes like potent celery. I like it.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-995\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191116.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191116\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nSome amazing types of peppers that haven\'t done anything exciting yet, but I know are definitely going to. There will be so many colors.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-994\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191106.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191106\" width=\"4032\" height=\"3024\" />\r\n\r\nBronze fennel. I ike to eat it a lot so I hope it grows.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-993\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191058.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191058\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nSome half dying basils in the back, cantaloupe, golden oregano, golden thyme, red sorrel. The sorrel has been growing great.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-992\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191049.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191049\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nItalian large leaf, one stalk survived. Thai is rocking, not as much as the one in the pot though. The boxwood basil died in the ground, too, but is killin it in the pot, so maybe it is shaded too much by the wall, but I don\'t know. I pruned it after transplanted and I think that killed the large leaf.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-990\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191043.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191043\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nCantaloupe starting to grow a little bit.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-989\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_191010.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_191010\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nParsley I am excited to eat. It is doing well. Hurry!!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-988\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190943.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190943\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nPapalo! A taste of lime and cilantro. Very good. Now get big and strong!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-987\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190938.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190938\" />\r\n\r\nPeruvian Black Mint. Very cool.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-986\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190931.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190931\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nSome Munstead Lavender.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-985\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190916.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190916\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nMint. It got dry and a bunch of leaves died. Now it has been watered but still looks bad compared to how I got it.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-984\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190908.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190908\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032\" />\r\n\r\nRed sorrel looking great.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-982\" src=\"http://journal.rruffles.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_20170425_190856.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_20170425_190856\" width=\"3024\" height=\"4032